title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook for 10 minutes.
Real good with dry beans.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage, set aside.
Beat eggs, add milk and salt.
In a greased 9x13 in. layer bread, sausage and cheese. Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: fried salmon puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep oil.
Fry until brown, turning once.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Fix cornbread mix according to directions on box.
Crumble cornbread in a large bowl.
Mix chopped bell pepper, tomatoes, onion and bacon.
Mix 1/2 cup sweet salad cubes, 1/4 cup of sweet pickle juice and 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: mrs. moore's spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well.
Pat with paper towels.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: speedy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Add water, eggs, oil, and food coloring,
Blend 2 minutes.
Makes 2 or 3 layers.
Bake at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pot; heat until warmed, but not boiling. Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: aunt hazel's punch cake
directions: Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat to blend.
Add vanilla and blend in.
Add dry ingredients and blend in, but do not overmix. Lastly, fold in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Turn batter into a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before turning out to cool on rack.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine the turkey, water, bouillon, onion, celery, salt, pepper, sage and vegetables. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook for 10 minutes. Stir in pasta. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally so pasta does not stick to bottom of pan. Makes about 10 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin pie mix.
Pour into 3 (9 x 4 x 1/2-inch) loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice-itself chocolate layer cake
directions: Line two 8-inch layer pans with foil; butter foil.
Combine coconut, pecans, brown sugar, 3 tablespoons melted butter, the evaporated milk and corn syrup in a small bowl.
Divide mixture and spread evenly over bottom of each pan.

title: coconut chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Grease cookie sheet. Combine milk and chocolate in double boiler over low heat. Stir frequently until chocolate has melted. Remove from heat and pour into mixing bowl. Stir in coconut, pecans, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake for about 15 minutes, or until firm.

title: chilled pineapple paella salad
directions: Sprinkle rice with curry powder and pineapple syrup.
Add mayonnaise, green onion, green bell pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well, cover and chill for at least one hour.
Thaw out the shrimp, sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add water to peas as package directs, bring to a boil and drain immediately.
Set aside 1/4 cup of peas for garnish.
Drain pineapple and set aside a few chunks for garnish.
Combine shrimp, peas, pineapple and ham; chill.
Before serving, drain any liquid from mixture and combine with rice. Spoon into lettuce-lined bowl and garnish.

title: surprise cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend the cottage cheese, Cool Whip and the dry gelatin (just lightly blend, folding it in).
Add fruit.
Many combinations possible.
For instance, Mandarin oranges and grapes.
If desired, add coconut, marshmallows and nuts.
May be served at once.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar;
add eggs one at a time, then mashed bananas.
Add
baking
powder and salt to the flour and sift 3 times.
Then
add
a little flour to the mixed butter, sugar, eggs and mashed bananas.
Then mix in the buttermilk, a little flour and 1/4 cup of hot water to which baking soda has been added. Dredge the chopped, toasted nuts in the remaining flour and
mix in
the
batter.
Then add vanilla.
Bake in 3 layer pans
that have been greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 375°
for
about 20
minutes.
After layers are cooked and cooled, use 7-minute icing
between
layers and on top.
Decorate with pecan halves or other ways.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in plate. Beat remaining ingredients; pour over ham, etc.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until firm and golden brown.

title: pineapple date bread
directions: Combine egg, milk, shortening, pineapple, nuts and dates.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and mix just enough to moisten.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: greek-style shrimp with rigatoni
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.
Add garlic and cook briefly, stirring.
Add tomatoes and cook 1 minute.
Add wine, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.

title: michael's fudgy no bakes
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop a spoonful on waxed paper to cool.

title: four bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except tomatoes, in a large pot.
Add 5 cups water.
Bring to a boil, and then lower the heat to a simmer. Cook until beans are soft.
Add tomatoes and more water to desired consistency.
Salt to taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine softened cheese and potatoes.
Mix until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(You can make the night before and bake it the next day.)

title: oklahoma watermelon punch
directions: Top watermelon and remove pulp.
Remove seeds.
Set watermelon cavity aside and remove enough hull for cavity to stand evenly. Process pulp in blender or processor in batches until smooth. Strain into large bowl until juices measure 7 cups.
Blend 1 1/2 pints of strawberries with sugar until smooth, about 15 seconds. Stir into watermelon juice with lemonade and vodka.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
When ready to serve, fill melon cavity with punch.
Top with sliced berries and garnish.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute peppers and onions in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add chopped meat and brown.
Mix rice and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll into bite size balls.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meatballs.
Add meatballs.
Put in a baking dish, and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: creamed brussels sprouts with onions
directions: Melt butter over medium-low heat in large saucepan.
Stir in flour with whisk wire brush.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 1 1/2 minutes until lightly brown.
Stir in soup and cream.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in Brussels sprouts and onions.
Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, and until vegetables are tender.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine flour, salt, soda and spices; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts. Drop dough by tablespoon, 3 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Allow to cool slightly on cookie sheets before removing.

title: oven cracker jacks
directions: Put popped corn in a buttered bowl and set aside.
Heat the margarine, corn syrup and brown sugar and bring to a boil.
Add cream of tartar and reduce heat.
Boil for 5 minutes (no more). Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over corn and stir well. Spread caramel corn on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 225° to 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Keeps well in sealed container.

title: herb bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix with 1 cup hot water the dill seed, caraway seed, mustard seed, celery seed, sesame seed, parsley flakes, garlic salt, salt and minced onion.

title: miss b's chocolate banana delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, pudding and milk in a bowl. Let set in refrigerator for 5 minutes. Take out; add Cool Whip and sour cream. In 9 x 13 dish, put a layer of vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas, layer of filling and then drizzle chocolate syrup over that. Repeat again on the filling; the last time, omit chocolate syrup. Grate a milk chocolate bar over the filling for decoration. (The candy bar will grate better if it has been chilled.)

title: chicken-mushroom bake
directions: Place chicken parts in flat baking dish.
Combine poultry and seasoning, chopped parsley, soup and sliced mushrooms.
Pour over chicken parts, bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: meat balls for spaghetti
directions: Put all ingredients together in a large bowl and mix well. Gather enough meat mixture in hands to form golf-size meat balls. Place meat balls in your own spaghetti sauce, using 1 quart of sauce.
Simmer at least 2 hours.
If using crock-pot, put on low heat 8 or 9 hours.
Makes 16 meat balls.
Cook 1/2 pound dry spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in large bowl 2 minutes.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: reception punch
directions: Take 2 cups of patience, one heart full of love, 2 handfuls of generosity and 1 dash of laughter.
Sprinkle with kindness.
Mix well.
Serve everyone you meet.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute diced beef in oleo until slightly browned.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Add chopped onion to meat saute. Add the flour and stir in the beef broth.
Bring to boil.
Add hot mustard and mushrooms.
Cover pan and simmer one hour.
Before serving, add the sour cream and Sauterne.
Do not boil after adding these last two ingredients.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Put butter, sugar and water in a pan and bring to boil.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips, vanilla and eggs.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Add remaining chocolate chips.
Put into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with vanilla pudding;
refrigerate 10 minutes.
Mix with sour cream and Cool Whip; add to pan.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light.
Add egg yolks, flour, baking powder, cracker crumbs, chopped nuts, dates and vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Put together with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan until done.

title: peanut-butterscotch bars
directions: Melt in a 3-quart saucepan the chips and peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Add Rice Krispies, mixing well. Press mixture in a 9 x 9 x 2 pan coated with cooking spray. Chill until firm. Cut and store in refrigerator.

title: bird's nest
directions: Mix cheese, beer and garlic salt in bowl with beater until creamy.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Scoop out center of round loaf and break bread into small dip-sized pieces.
Arrange on serving dish around loaf.
Spoon cheese mixture into center of loaf.
Use bread pieces to dip cheese.
Great for an extra at parties or as a snack.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and let cool. Crumble cornbread in bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate beef in it.
Freeze the sirloin tip roast slightly.
Then as it thaws, slice very thin. Marinate the sliced beef in the sauce at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.
Grill 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, vanilla, shortening and 1/2 of the cake mix (dry) until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (centers will be soft).
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: svenska pepparkakor(swedish gingerbread christmas cookies)
directions: Whip butter, sugar and syrup together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix into a nice dough.
Let it rest in the refrigerator until the next day.
Roll out the dough thin (3 mm) and cut out hearts, animals, etc. and set on a buttered surface. Place on baking sheets and bake at 175°C for 7 to 10 minutes, or until they have a nice brown color.
You can decorate with sugar icing if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip pudding mix and milk; add 1/2 container Cool Whip and Eagle Brand to pudding mixture.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas with pudding mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix melted butter and brown sugar. Set aside.
Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits in half.
Roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop into Bundt pan.
After each layer of biscuits pour butter and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Line small muffin pan cups (each 1 3/4 x 1-inch) with fluted paper cups that have 1 1/4-inch bases and are 1-inch high.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in other ingredients. Chill until firm.
Serve.

title: coconut chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Note:
Crush up tomatoes with your hands.

title: grilled maryland hard shell crab
directions: Back and clean uncooked crab.
Make mixture of Old Bay and melted butter or margarine.
Baste crab with mixture.
Place over hot coals on grill.
Keep basting until done.

title: apple noodles
directions: Combine apples with sugar and cinnamon.
In casserole dish, combine boiled noodles with apple mixture.
Dot with butter on top.
(Optional:
We usually add cooked, sliced sausage to mixture or you can serve sausage as a side dish.)
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chops casserole
directions: Put browned pork chops in 2 layers in a casserole dish with sliced onion, potatoes and carrots.
Add can of soup.
Add water to cover meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until desired consistency.

title: flight line savory pork roast or loin
directions: Marinate pork loin with Worcestershire sauce in bag or bowl overnight.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Combine into an ice cream freeze the drinks, milk and pineapple.
Freeze until hard.

title: creamy sweet slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery and green pepper. Stir together sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, evaporated milk, salt and pepper; pour over cabbage mixture and mix well. Chill until serving time.

title: pepper burgers
directions: Shape beef into 4 (1/2-inch thick) patties.
Place patties on grill over medium coals.
Grill seven to nine minutes for medium, turning patties once during cooking.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix together boiling water and bran buds cereal.
Let cool.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Melt chocolate squares in microwave.
Mix ingredients together and pour into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
"Yummy-yummy!"

title: california club salad
directions: Cover a large platter with lettuce.
On the lettuce, arrange chicken, eggs, bacon, tomato wedges and avocado.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until light; add milk. Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in oil.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine in a saucepan cranberries, orange, juice, water and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add one-half of the marshmallows and the cherry Jell-O.
Stir and let cool.
Add the celery, nuts, pineapple and the remaining marshmallows.
Set in refrigerator to chill until serving time.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter or margarine.
Cut with a pie cutter or fork until very fine.
Stir in milk.
Roll on floured board to desired thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or a glass.
Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with pineapple, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Put mixture into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool loaf 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Place sirloin tips in crock-pot. Spoon soup over meat. Add onion and green pepper, if desired. Cover and cook on low setting and your dinner will be ready when you get home!

title: chicken cheese melt away casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened.
Place half macaroni in greased 2-quart casserole dish and half chicken over macaroni.
Repeat.
Arrange cheese on top, pour sauce over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir all ingredients with spoon.
Roll and cut and bake until golden brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Place ice cream and sherbet in punch bowl and add liquid.
May add vodka.

title: greek seasoned chicken with orzo(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Add chicken; seal and marinate in the refrigerator 30 minutes.

title: date pecan rolls
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and syrup to soft ball stage when dropped into cold water.
Add dates and heat until thick.
Add pecans.
Turn out on damp cloth and roll in log.
Chill, then slice.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in lime water.	Wash once.
Let stand 3 hours in cold water. Place cucumbers in mixture of remaining ingredients and let stand 12 hours or overnight.
Heat 35 minutes in syrup.
Place in jars and seal. DO NOT BOIL!

title: danish puff pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in oil.
Place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Keep them warm. Meanwhile, in small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or margarine; add flour.
Cook and stir for 1 minute; add milk. Stirring, bring to a boil and boil until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat in egg until smooth.
Stir in onion and cheese.
Over low heat, cook and stir just until cheese melts.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce over each pork chop, spreading to edges.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes or just until chops are done and cheese is puffed and golden.
Makes 4 chops.

title: grace's cold oven cake
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl all at once.
Beat for 20 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased angel food pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Heat oven after putting in cake.

title: peanut butter cup brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as per brownie cake style brownies (2 eggs).
Use regular muffin tins with shallow liners or cut down deeper ones.
Use 1 measuring tablespoon of batter for each.
In center, gently press unwrapped peanut butter cup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tailgate salad
directions: Place in layers in order written.
Spread mayonnaise on each layer. Sprinkle each layer with sugar.
If you like the bacon crisp when served, wait until you serve before putting bacon in or on dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in shortening.
Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Mix well; add buttermilk and mix again.
Place in a covered container in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with desired size biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
A minute or two before done, brush tops with melted butter.
These freeze well.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and chopped nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix well and press flat in bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°; let cool.
Combine cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread over crust and cool.
Combine pudding and milk; mix well and spread over cream cheese layer.
Cool.
Spread whipped topping over pudding layer.
Sprinkle top with pecans. Can be frozen.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.

title: corn tofu slices
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Combine cornmeal, garlic and herbs. Cut tofu in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place slices, one at a time, in cornmeal mixture and coat evenly.
Place in frying pan and brown both sides.
Use in sandwiches with pickles, tomatoes, lettuce, mustard, etc.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes in cake with utility fork.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Saute onions and pepper.
Add all to pot in order, sauteing onions and pepper while others heat.
Simmer on low heat 20 minutes.
Serve over bed of cooked rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Shred 3 1/2 cups Golden Delicious apples. Place them in freezer bag and freeze until needed. Measure 3 cups again. Mix all ingredients. Grease and flour oblong pan, about 8 1/2 x 15. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Test with toothpick.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes. Add pimento, mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Mash bananas in blender.
Mix with all other ingredients and freeze.
Let stand about 2 hours.
Before serving, pour 6 to 12 ounces of Sprite over and serve.

title: spicy tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water for a drink.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef.
Add salt and pepper to taste, chili powder, onion, sugar, ground cloves and tomato juice.
Mix well and add red kidney beans and pinto beans.
Simmer about 20 minutes and serve.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine ingredients and melt cheese mixture in double boiler pan over hot water.

title: chicken divine
directions: Place cooked, drained broccoli in a shallow, greased baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover with cheese, then top with bread crumbs or potato chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seasoned pan-baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer in baking pan. Cover with onion. Add margarine slices and bacon pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with Season-All. Cover with water and put foil over pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When potatoes are done, uncover and turn oven up to 450° for 10 minutes to brown potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together using only 1/2 of melted butter. (Hash browns do not have to be thawed.)
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan or glass dish.
Mix corn flake crumbs with remaining melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers (do not peel).
Slice thinly (1/4 to 1/8-inch thick).
Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain well and wash with cold water in morning.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and alum in a large pot.
Bring to boil; add drained vegetables and return to full boil.
Pack in hot sterilized jars covering vegetables with hot syrup and seal. Yield:
6 pints.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Put rice, water and salt into heavy 2-quart saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat until water boils. Reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender (about 15 minutes). Remove from heat. Stir in milk and raisins. Beat eggs just until blended. Add gradually, while stirring briskly, to rice-milk mixture. Return to low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a metal spoon. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla extract and nutmeg. Serve hot or cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onion, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Divide and put into two greased pie pans or one 9 x 13-inch casserole. (Don't make casserole too thick or too deep.)
Cover with a topping made with crushed corn flakes and 1 stick margarine, melted.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fudgy no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to a boil. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool and then enjoy!

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Boil noodles in salted water.
Meanwhile, beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and cream.
When well blended, beat in cheese, salt and plenty of black pepper.
Drain noodles well; toss with sauce.
Serve immediately with a sprinkling of more cheese on top.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter and add flour, baking powder, sugar and milk. Mix well. Pour in 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 baking dish (greased). Add fruit on top; do NOT stir. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza with oat bran crust
directions: Combine oat bran, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and oil; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly spray 12-inch round pizza pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of oat bran.
With lightly oiled fingers, pat dough out evenly.
Shape edge to form rim.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Spread sauce over partially baked crust.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes more.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together.
Dip apples in the caramel mixture.
If you like, then dip into chopped peanuts.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in 2 or 3 tablespoons of butter.
Cook rice as directed.
Mix all ingredients together. Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Half recipe for a smaller portion.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Brown ground meat with onion in skillet. Season to taste. Put in the bottom of a 4 or 5-quart pan. Then add sliced potatoes, carrots, peppers, rice and tomatoes on the top. Layer in that order. Cover and bake at 350° about 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and vanilla pudding.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs. Add morsels.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a small amount of oleo. Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well, and
pour over top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: poluorones - mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 c. powered sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour, pecans and salt. Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 325° oven 20 - 25 minutes till lightly browned.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.
Sprinkle with additional chopped pecans if desired.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Prepare marinade with lime juice, soy sauce and olive oil; cover chicken and refrigerate several hours.
Turn every now and then.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: In a large glass bowl, mix lemon juice, vegetable oil, vinegar, oregano and garlic powder.
Place chicken pieces in bowl, season with salt and pepper.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: light jello fruit sponge dessert
directions: Place sliced strawberries on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Make large package of jello and pour over strawberries.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Once set, slice sponge cake into 1-inch slices and place on top of set jello mixture.
Poke holes in sponge cake.
Make small package of jello and pour it over sponge cake-jello mixture.
Refrigerate.
Once total jello mixture is set, top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with whole strawberries.
Great refreshing summertime dessert.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: heart smart cake
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Drain fruit well.
Reserve 3/4 cup fruit juice, adding water if necessary.
Heat juice.
Stir in the gelatin until dissolved, then add the fruit.
Chill.
When gelatin mixture begins to thicken, fold in the yogurt.
Split the angel food cake horizontally in thirds and fill each layer with fruit as you re-stack cake.
Frost with Smooth N' Creamy Frosting.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with bread.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add milk and remaining ingredients. Mix well. Always start in a cold oven. Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad ii
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients 1/2 hour before serving. Mix with broccoli and other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: english pea salad
directions: Layer vegetables in large bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over salad. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate, covered with Saran Wrap, overnight.

title: cucumber tomato salad(makes 6 servings; carb count: 5 grams)
directions: *Distilled white vinegar may be substituted for rice vinegar. **May substitute 4 1/2 packets Equal| sweetener.

title: cheesy shrimp biscuits(makes 20)
directions: Bake biscuits according to directions.
Split in half.
Place shrimp on biscuits.
Mix together mayonnaise, onions and Parmesan cheese; spread over shrimp.
Cover with Swiss cheese and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place under broiler until golden brown and bubbly.

title: riviera peaches
directions: Place 2 peach halves in each dessert dish.
Melt jelly over low heat.
Pour over peaches.
Chill 2 hours.
Just before serving, top with scoops of ice cream.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture in center of each tortilla and spread evenly.
Roll up and chill.

title: spaghetti sauce for 100
directions: Chop onions; brown lightly in oil.
Add meat; cook until pinkness is gone (I brown the meat in the oven).
Add other ingredients; simmer for 4 hours.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Put apple juice and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir to dissolve sugar; add spices, cover and boil 5 minutes.
Remove spices, lower heat and simmer.
An orange or lemon slice may be used to garnish each cup.
Serves approximately 24.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip-peanut butter cup cookies
directions: You will need 1 package of mini muffin liners.

title: beef and potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes and dice in small pieces.
Put in pan and cover with water.
Add onions and sliced carrots.
Cook for fifteen minutes.
Add corned beef and cook until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg, onions and cheese together.
Add broccoli to mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake until formed and golden.
Put onion rings on top. Bake until onion rings are golden.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl. Add milk, vanilla, butter and pecans (if using).
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except water; sprinkle this dry mixture over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonful on a well-greased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken breasts in melted oleo.
Roll in cracker crumbs. Place in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until done.
Test with fork.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix flour with a little of the milk, then mix all ingredients together.
Put in a well-greased baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place butter, onion, garlic and green pepper in a deep 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole and heat on Full power 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well to combine.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power, 2 minutes or until sauce bubbles.
Serve over meat or poultry. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: buckeyes candy
directions: Make into balls and dip into melted chocolate chips (16 ounce bag).

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cream 1/2 cup of sugar and margarine together.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Pack down on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Spread blueberry filling evenly on top.
Add whipped cream and refrigerate several hours.

title: german chocolate balls
directions: Mix and bake cake according to pkg. directions using a 9 x 13 inch pan. Cool cake and crumble in pan. Stir box of frosting into cake crumbs and make 1 inch balls. Place on a cookie sheet and chill. Melt bark in double boiler and dip chilled balls into bark. Cool on wax paper.

title: old fashioned yellow cake
directions: Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Frost as desired.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Layer potatoes and onion slices in baking dish.
Put pork chops on top.
Spoon soup over top and add 2 cans of water.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are done.

title: jingle bell's cake
directions: Mix well!
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until done.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine squash and water in a large microwavable bowl. Cover with plastic wrap; vent. Microwave on high for 6 minutes. Drain well. Place bread in food processor and pulse 10 times or until coarse crumbs form to measure 1 cup. Combine the squash, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, sour cream, cheese, salt, pepper and soup. Spoon squash mixture into a 2 quart casserole coated with cooking spray. Top with the remaining bread crumbs. Spray breadcrumbs with cooking spray. Bake for 30 minutes. Makes 12 servings. 85 calories, 1 g. fat, 1 g. fiber.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out into cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread mixture on cooled crescent crust.
Top with vegetables listed or any other of your favorite vegetables.
Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal pie("a poor man's pecan pie")
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in syrup, vanilla and oatmeal.
Pour mixture into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add other ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 8 hours.

title: barbecue delight
directions: Bring ingredients, except chuck roast or chickens, to a boil; cool slightly.
Pour over chuck roast or chickens and marinate overnight and following day.
Cook over hot coals.
Baste as it cooks.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread; don't allow it to raise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear (or cut) one loaf into pieces and drop into pan.
Melt butter, add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over the bread.
Tear up second loaf and put on top.
Try to piece in any empty spots.
Let raise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin walnut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add raisins, walnuts and vanilla.

title: burrito bake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer other ingredients and top with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut potatoes into quarters. Place in a large saucepan with enough water to cover potatoes. Bring to a boil on high heat. Cook until tender, about 8 minutes; drain well.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers and vinegar and puree in blender of food processor in 2 or 3 batches.
Combine puree with sugar and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add food coloring and remove from heat.
Add Certo and stir well.
Return to heat and boil for 1 minute.
Strain through sieve and skim off any foam. Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: grandma's sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until the meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the ketchup, relish and brown sugar; mix well. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until heated through. Spoon onto buns. Yields 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients; put in zucchini.
Spoon into two floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May want to check after 45 minutes.
Done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Follow directions for hot roll mix.
Knead and roll about to size of a cookie sheet, 1/4-inch thick.
Place pepperoni, side by side, on top of dough.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll, jelly roll fashion.
Seal edges and fold under ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out pan and apply butter to top and sides of loaf.
Continue baking 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into slices and serve.
Serves 6 to 8. We like to dip this into Ranch dressing.

title: green bean and rice casserole
directions: Cook green beans with chopped onion for about 30 minutes or until onion is slightly cooked.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of bean liquid.
Add green beans, rice, cheese and pimentos.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbling.

title: mock chicken pie
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients in oil.
Mix all together and cover with pie crust.
Bake until golden brown.

title: tiny raisin-apple loaf
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in milk and lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture just until moistened.
Stir in raw apple and raisins.
Spoon batter into 3 greased 6 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook the brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and water to 235°; stir until 260°.
Add the salt; stir to 275°.

title: pineapple pecan pizza
directions: Prepare crust by mixing crushed Rice Krispies, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cheese, flour, milk and eggs into cooked squash.
Add salt and sugar.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish; top with bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together in large casserole dish.
Season with Cavender's Greek seasoning (you can't put too much).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: glorified banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and half of Cool Whip. In a large pan, put 1 layer of wafers, one layer of bananas and layer of pudding mix.
Repeat this once more.
Put other half of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Chill.

title: wagon wheel stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In large saucepan, brown meat and garlic in the oil.
Stir in water, tomatoes, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, onions and bay leaf.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery and pasta.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners in small muffin pan or on cookie sheet.

title: zesty crab salad
directions: Marinate the first 5 ingredients for about 1 hour.
Toss chilled Creamettes and marinated mixture together with mayonnaise, then add tomatoes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, jello, cornstarch and water to boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Place sliced and washed berries in baked pie shell.
Pour filling over berries.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: a christmas salad
directions: Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Put on top of Jell-O that has jelled.
Add Cool Whip on top.

title: easy scampi
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet over low heat.
Add onion, garlic and parsley.
Saute until golden, about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and stir just until pink.
Remove shrimp and place in ovenproof dish.
Cover lightly and keep warm.
Add wine and lemon juice to skillet and simmer about 2 to 3 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; pour over shrimp and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Break eggs in bowl.
Add oil and mix together.
Mix in milk. Add sifted dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in microwave until thick. Pour in cooked shell. Add meringue and bake.

title: pineapple bread casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs. Stir in undrained pineapple. Add bread and mix well. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. This is a great side dish to serve with ham.

title: baked zucchini slices
directions: Drain cooked squash.
Combine all ingredients with squash and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bob hall's irish rebel bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Melt margarine and pour half in bottom of greased bread pan.
Add dough and pour remaining margarine over the top.
Bake in pre-heated oven at 350° for one hour.
(Serve with Irish Stew).

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add honey, lemon juice, vinegar and onion.
Stir.
Pour into blender, cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
While blender is running, slowly pour in oil through opening in cover.
Stop.
Pour into a container and stir in poppy seed.
Makes 1 pint dressing.
This dressing will not separate.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown together hamburger, taco or chili seasoning and onion. Put meat mixture in the bottom of a large casserole dish and add the remaining ingredients in layers.
Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes, covered.

title: oven fried eggplant
directions: Pare and slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
(Salt may be omitted for low salt diet.) Dip in milk, then roll in flour.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 375° oven until crisp, turning once.
Remove from oven and spread margarine on each slice while still hot, if desired.

title: meadow muffins
directions: Cook beef, green pepper and onion until meat is brown.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
Crumble the bread and add to the meat mixture along with the barbecue sauce (or ketchup).

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cut into dice, cold, Irish potatoes; have them not too well done.

Put in a skillet a large lump of butter, a tablespoon of flour; let them cream together, not fry, then gently stir in milk; when it is hot, but in potatoes and season with salt and pepper. Shake the pan so they will not brown.
Keep covered.
When the potatoes are heated through, dish up.

title: boston lettuce and mandarin salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into bite size pieces.
Refrigerate. Make dressing by mixing the next 9 ingredients in a pint glass jar. Chill several hours, then shake well.
Before serving, mix lettuce and dressing, then toss in oranges, avocado and walnuts.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients with electric mixer; chill. Serve with bite-sized pieces of fresh fruit.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine margarine, dates and sugar into saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat, add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: no bake snowballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to first ingredients until mixed.
Then spread between 2 vanilla wafers until all used.
Place on trays.
Put trays in freezer until cookies are frozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and put in airtight containers.
To use, add and stir 1/3 cup (or to taste) of hot chocolate mix to cup of hot water.

title: easy frozen yogurt
directions: In medium-size bowl, mix all ingredients.
Freeze for about 4 hours, stirring hourly for the first 3 hours.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients together.
Mix a little at a time, adding milk when mixture becomes dry.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: curry cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and sour cream. Add other ingredients. Form ball and wrap in Saran Wrap.
When ready to serve, roll in toasted coconut.
Leave at room temperature about 1/2 hour before serving. Pour about 1/2 cup Major Grey's chutney over.
Serve with crackers. Make at least 2 days ahead for flavors to mix.

title: linda's low-fat lasagna
directions: Spray fry pan with cooking spray.
Saute garlic and onion. Add ground beef until browned.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan, spread small amount of sauce on bottom.
Layer in the following order: raw lasagna noodles, ground beef, Ricotta, sprinkle bacon bits, Mozzarella and sprinkle grated cheese.
Repeat 2 more times.
Pour water around sides of pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 20 minutes to set before serving.

title: crock-pot chicken and ham
directions: Wrap ham slice around chicken breast and cheese slice, use toothpicks to hold together.
Put in crock-pot and pour undiluted mushroom soup over top (soup will thin and form juice during cooking).
Set crock-pot on high for 2 hours, turn to low setting for 5 to 6 additional hours.
Spoon sour cream over all the last 15 minutes of cooking.
Great served with wild rice.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla in a bowl; mix well.
Place bread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan and pour mixture over.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mother's banana pudding
directions: Cook in double boiler the milk, sugar, flour, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour over the bananas. Makes 1 pie.

title: booze slush
directions: Boil water, tea bags and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients and blend together.
Freeze.
When ready to use, scoop into glass and add 7-Up.

title: whippersnaps cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat with mixer.
Add flour, carrots, cinnamon and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° in 3 (9-inch) pans for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with prunes and port
directions: In small bowl, steep prunes and Port for 10 minutes.
Add broth and set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Add pork chops sprinkled with salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Add prune mixture with remaining 1 tablespoon butter in skillet. Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon over pork chops; sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or microwave until bubbles.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: To rhubarb, add 2 cups water.
Cook until tender.
Add sugar and Jell-O; dissolve.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: quick money bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and place in bowl.
Pour melted butter over biscuit, tossing to coat.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over pieces, gently mixing just until coated.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then invert on plate.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in just enough mayonnaise to blend ingredients.
Refrigerating before serving is best.

title: ugly cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to instructions on box.
Pour in pan.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cake.
Do not smooth out.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Turn out on foil-lined cookie sheet.
If any sticks to pan, use a spatula to place on cake.

title: mint bars
directions: Mix all ingredients until fluffy creamy.
Spread on top of crust.
Put back in refrigerator until you have your chocolate melted.
Leave in until firm.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine everything except orange slices.
Stud orange slices with cloves.
Put orange slices in cups and pour cider over them.

title: spanish peanut cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder and beat into other ingredients well.
Add corn flakes, rolled oats, Spanish peanuts and chocolate bits.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Combine milk, egg and shortening or oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at about 350° for about 1 hour. Check at 40 minutes.

title: beef short ribs
directions: Heat the oil in a Dutch oven or electric skillet on medium high heat.
Mix the flour, salt and pepper together.
Coat the ribs with the flour mixture, then place them in the hot oil and brown on all sides.
When all are brown, drain the oil.
Add the water and onions to the skillet or Dutch oven; cover tightly. Reduce the heat to medium and let the ribs cook for 2 hours or until tender.
Or, after adding the water and onions, cook the ribs in the oven at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve on rice.
Serves 6.

title: ham hocks and collard greens
directions: Pick and wash greens.
Roll up collard leaf and cut up.
Cook ham hocks until tender.
Add collard greens and 1/2 teaspoon of ground red pepper.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Good with hot corn bread.

title: batter buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg and 1 cup flour; mix well.
Add remaining flour.
Beat until smooth. Spoon in greased muffin tins.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Drain liquid from corn and put corn in a greased baking dish. Mix sugar, eggs and flour to make a paste.
Mix paste with corn. Add salt to taste.
Pour milk over corn mixture and stir.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions until done.
Add tomatoes, beans and salt. Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn bread mixture (prepare according to directions on package).
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: cascade potato casserole
directions: In a small skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and cook until tender.
In large bowl, beat undiluted soup and cheese together until smooth.
Stir in salt, pepper, onion and potatoes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix; form into ball.
Garnish with pieces of dried beef or roll in chopped nut meats.

title: rigatoni pepperoni
directions: Lightly brown rigatoni in frying pan. Add tomato sauce and simmer while rigatoni noodles are cooking.
Drain noodles when done and layer sauce, noodles and cheese 4 to 5 times in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: death by chocolate 1
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Make chocolate pudding and mousse and let set.
Cool cake, then cut into small pieces.
In a large bowl put some of cake pieces, scoops of the pudding, mousse and Cool Whip.
Crack candy bars into small pieces and sprinkle.
Continue making layers until you use up all the ingredients.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes and pour in 10-inch pan.
Drain sliced peaches.
Place fruit over batter (save juice). Mix for 2 minutes cream cheese, 4 tablespoons fruit juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spoon over fruit and batter.
Keep 1/2-inch from edge. Mix cinnamon and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cake will not look done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in ball and then in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate ball.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans. Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry. Set aside. In a medium bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir to mix.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar, beating well.
Add the vanilla and almond extracts.
Mix well.

Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, starting and ending with the flour. Fold the egg whites into the batter. Spoon into prepared pans and bake for about 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of layers comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately and cool completely on racks before frosting.

title: crabbies
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Cut muffins into eighths.

title: vegetable fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve on crisp lettuce or glass dish.

title: old-fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt real good.
Add boiling water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add butter and cook until melted.
Add small amount of cooked mixture to beaten eggs and mix.
Put back into mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove; add vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: busy day beef soup
directions: Crumble beef; put all in kettle.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat for 1 minute.

Add the green pepper, celery, onion and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, until the onion is soft, about 5 minutes. Add the rice and cook, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes longer or until the rice is golden.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating about 10 minutes or until very light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition and scraping bowl often.

title: watermelon basket
directions: Cut watermelon lengthwise, slicing off top third.
Use larger piece for fruit holder.
Scoop out melon balls with melon ball cutter or measuring teaspoon.
Scallop top edge of shell.
Fill with watermelon, cantaloupe and honeydew melon balls.
Add strawberries.
Pour pineapple juice over top.
Tuck in grape leaves or mint.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, Pet milk, broccoli and rice.
Bake 30 minutes; put cheese on top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: christmas potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter and milk in small saucepan until butter melts.
Do not boil.
Combine potatoes, peppers, onions, pimento, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour on milk and butter.
Bake 3 to 4 hours.
Milk may be added during cooking if needed.
Top with cheese or corn flake crumb topping the last 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares; serve each piece on lettuce leaf and add small drop of mayonnaise on top. Yields 12 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook pasta until done, throw in the rest of the ingredients. Chill and serve.
Great for picnics!

title: turkey burgers with mushrooms
directions: In a medium bowl, combine turkey, garlic, paprika and black pepper.
Shape into four 3/4-inch thick burgers.
Place burgers on hot grill.
Grill for 3 minutes.
Turn burgers over and cook until patties are no longer pink, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry sauce
directions: Combine berries and sugar in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Drain, reserving juice.
Set berries aside.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until thoroughly cooked.
Remove meat from bones. Place chicken meat in bowl and sprinkle with cumin.
Heat green chili in frying pan, just until warm.
Moisten tortillas in green chili.
Place approximately 3 spoonfuls of chicken in a tortilla and roll up.
Place rolled tortilla in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat until pan is full, about 12 to 14 tortillas.
Pour remaining green chili over top.
Cover with cheese and olives.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with chopped tomatoes and/or sour cream.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place ham and water in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is nearly tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer until vegetables are done. Add water, if necessary.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Add cut up shrimp to softened cream
cheese,
blend
in seasoning.
Mix well and work into ball with hands.
Roll ball in chopped pecans to cover.
Serve with crackers.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve un-iced.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: jumbo cornburger
directions: Combine the 2 eggs, tomato sauce, Worcestershire, 3/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Spread half the meat mixture in an 8 x 11 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Combine 1 egg, corn, cracker crumbs, green pepper, onion, pimiento, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sage; spoon over meat.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
The last 5 minutes, arrange tomato slices on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple beef jerky
directions: Place butter and soy sauce in frying pan and bring to a boil. Place slices in pan and cook until brown on both sides and in center.
Keep adding soy sauce until the meat soaks it up.
Place take into consideration that meat shrinks up a little.
Serve hot, warm or cold.
Makes only 1 serving.

title: franks in tomato gravy
directions: Saute vegetables and add to stewed tomatoes.
Add franks to stewed tomatoes and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: banana walnut bread(recipe for bread machine)
directions: Place ingredients in the bread machine pan in the order suggested by the manufacturer. Select Basic bread cycle and start machine. Makes one 1 1/2-pound loaf.

title: pumpkin spice cake with creamy icing
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil and mix at medium speed until there is no visible trace of oil (at least 3 minutes).
Add flour and spices, then add pumpkin and mix at a slower speed until the batter is well blended.
Pour into greased Bundt pan (or in two round pans for double layer cake).
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (less time for two round pans).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in pan.
To lower fat grams, rinse meat with hot water.
Add packages of seasoning to meat.
Mix well.
Add tomato sauce, then water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer about 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add fruit of choice, vanilla and milk last.
Mix well.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
In a blender, blend cottage cheese until smooth; pour into a large bowl and add the cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat until evenly blended.
Add eggs, beating until well mixed.
Pour into an 8 inch square baking dish. Bake 40-45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Meanwhile in a small bowl, combine the sour cream, remaining 1/4 cup sugar and the vanilla; mix well.
Remove the cake from the oven and spread the sour cream mixture evenly over the top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Allow to cool, then cut into squares.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Place bread cubes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Crumble sausage over bread; top with grated cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with A.1. steak sauce or ketchup.

title: prize butter bars
directions: Beat well and spoon here and there on warm crust.
Spread. Sprinkle with chips, then with reserved crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raspberry jam bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumbs mix into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Spread jam evenly over top.
Cover with remaining crumbs and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours in a covered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Just before serving, add Cheddar cheese and melt in oven.
Then serve.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: Wash, peel and dice peaches.
Combine all ingredients including peaches.
Bring slowly to a boil; boil uncovered for 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: black forest dessert
directions: Make instant pudding (use only 1 cup of milk in pudding).
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Place on pie crust.
Surround pie with remaining Cool Whip leaving center free.
Fill center with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients well; fill in crust.

title: cool whip pie with fruit
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Mix everything together.
Pour in graham crust.
Place in freezer until hard.

title: nutty butty pies
directions: Cream the cream cheese, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Divide the mixture into the 3 pie crusts.
Sprinkle with nuts and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Freeze.
Cut while frozen. Eat and enjoy.

title: crab delight salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, lemon juice and rind. Mix and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

Mix 1 box instant lemon pudding as directed on box, only use 1/2 cup less milk. Pour over cooled bars. You can use cooked lemon pudding too. Top with cream cheese frosting. I use lemon juice instead of milk.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes long enough to peel jackets off of them. Cut in quarters. Lay in flat casserole baking dish. Make syrup (boil 3 or 4 minutes, take off heat and add butter and flavoring). Pour over potato quarters. Cook in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: farmer's stew(low cholesterol, low sodium)
directions: Simmer vegetables in large saucepan until done.
Brown turkey in skillet; drain off any fat.
Add vegetables and chili powder. Add pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: country club dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and thin with vinegar until of desired consistency.
Serve on a tossed green salad.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: baked fish (light)
directions: Thaw fish.
Place fish in casserole dish.
Combine onion, mushrooms, dressing and lemon.
Pour over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 4 servings; 178 calories, 5 grams of fat and 60 mg. cholesterol.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (only 1/4 cup mashed raspberries and 1/4 cup basil).
Pour over chicken breasts.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 2 hours before cooking.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with 1/4 cup whole raspberries and 1/4 cup basil.

title: carrot bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and top crust is deep golden brown.
Cool 15 minutes. Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 loaf (16 slices).

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans 10 to 12 hours.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Add salt.
Add garlic powder, oregano and bay leaf.
Saute onion and pepper in 1/2 of oil.
Add to beans and vinegar.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Add rice and remaining oil.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, vegetables first.
Mix well. Chill.

title: guava jelly
directions: Peel guavas and cut into squares.
Add sugar to top and let sit for 8 hours, until sugar has dissolved.
Add the water and boil for 2 hours.
Let sit until cool.
Strain juice into another container.
Check to see if guavas are thick enough.
If not, cook 30 more minutes.

title: girl scout punch
directions: Use ice cubes or (in a punch bowl) an ice ring made of frozen cranberry juice.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Slice apples; put in bowl.
Pour in other ingredients in order given.
Add a little butter.
Stir and pour into crust. Cook at 425° for 15 minutes, then cook for about 45 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 30 minutes covered at 350°. Remove from oven.
Mix 1/4 pound Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick melted oleo.
Sprinkle over casserole and return to oven until slightly brown.

title: jimmy carter
directions: Make a crumb crust by combining graham crackers and butter. Press into an oblong cake pan.

title: pistachio sour cream bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if Pyrex).
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs, oil and water.
Beat well until smooth.
In a small bowl, toss together cinnamon and nuts.
Divide batter between 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, alternating layers of batter with sugar-nut mixture.
End with a sugar layer.
Bake 1 hour or until loaves test done.
(Electric oven, 45 to 50 minutes.)

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together beef, oil and garlic.
Add canned tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil and parsley flakes.
Simmer 1 hour until thick.
Mix together cottage cheese, beaten eggs, pepper, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.

title: apple spicy muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix milk, apple juice concentrate, egg whites and oil.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients.
Add chopped apple, raisins, nuts and mix all together.	Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.	Fill with batter.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes.
After cooling, may store in plastic bag to retain moisture (in refrigerator).

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Put rice in bottom of pan. Mix milk and soups together; pour over rice. Sprinkle instant chicken bouillon (about 1 teaspoon) over it. Cut up chicken and lay over rice. Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over this. Sprinkle with paprika and cover tight with foil. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: jambalaya mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Place 1 2/3 c rice mix into each of flour air tight containers or plastic bag.
Makes 6 2/3 c rice mix.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine spices, blending well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well. (Mixture will be stiff.)
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Using small or medium size cookie cutters, cut dough into desired shapes.
Peel away excess dough and reroll as necessary.
Use a toothpick to make a hole in each ornament.
Let dry naturally, about a week.
You might use a utensil to flip the ornament over after a couple of days to dry on the back side.
Pull length of ribbon through hole of ornament. When completely dry, ornaments may be sealed in a plastic bag or tin.
Yields 15 to 20 ornaments.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead like dough.
Add food coloring if desired.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute; gradually add broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in pepper.
Add beer, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Ready to serve.

title: baymee syamee (okra)ahlen wah sahlen:  the door is open-welcome.
directions: Wash and trim okra not too close to the top.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, let stand 20 minutes.
Make sauce by frying onions lightly in the oil, add tomatoes and water and parsley, simmer awhile.
Then put half the tomato sauce on the bottom of casserole; drain okra, put on top sauce.
Cover with rest sauce, season, cover and bake in slow oven 300° for 1/2 hour until okra is tender.
Can be cooked on top stove.
This serves 4 people.
Delicious.

title: egg noodles
directions: Use the amounts of ingredients shown for each cup of flour. Put flour in bowl; make well in center.
Add egg, water and salt; mix first with fork, then with hands.
Form into ball; roll out on floured board (thin).
Let rest; cut into 4 equal pieces and stack.
Cut in strips, whatever width you want.
Separate noodles. Let dry several hours.
Use or store for later use.

title: chocolate chip nut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
To creamed mixture, add dates (liquid and all) and dry ingredients. Beat until well mixed.
Add vanilla and beat.
Pour into a cookie sheet with sides greased and floured.
Mix together chocolate chips, 3/4 cup sugar and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over top of cake. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: cheese onion bread
directions: Brown slightly
the onion in small amount of margarine.
Stir until moistened the remaining ingredients along with onion.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon poppy seed.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Combine all ingredients at least 1 day in advance so flavor can blend. Serve with raw flowered cauliflower and carrot sticks. Makes about 2 cups.

title: crispy oven baked chicken
directions: Remove excess fat from chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients in a
large bowl.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture until completely coated.
Place
in	a baking pan, skin side up, and brush all pieces with melted butter.	Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done and golden brown.

title: aussie burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into 8 patties. Grill or broil until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken until done, drain off broth in pan that you will be cooking dumplings in. Debone chicken and set aside. Mix 1 egg into 2 c. broth, mix in plain flour until a stiff dough. Roll out on dough board very thin, cut in strips, drop in very hot broth, cook until done. Add the deboned chicken. The secret is stiff dough.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix whipped topping, instant pudding and pineapple together. Fold in last 3 ingredients and refrigerate in a covered dish.

title: ooey-gooey bars
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Pour chocolate chips over the mixture. Blend the remaining eggs, confectioners sugar and cream cheese on medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Pour over chips. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Chill.
Nuts are optional.

title: mexi-veg rice salad
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Increase heat to medium and stir in rice.
Saute until rice is golden brown.
Stir in water, chicken soup mix and Mexican Blend.
Cook, stirring often, until water is absorbed and rice is tender.
Drain off any remaining liquid.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Cool completely.

title: pork barbecue sandwiches
directions: Boil and shred pork.
Place in tightly lidded skillet with remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: heavenly cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers and melted margarine in small mixing bowl.
Press mixture into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes; cool.

title: baked grapefruit
directions: Prepare grapefruit sprinkling brown sugar over each half. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave each half 40 to 60 seconds on High.
(May be used as appetizer or dessert.) Just before serving, place cherry in center of each half.

title: quick turkey dinner
directions: In a bowl, combine turkey, bread crumbs and egg until blended. Shape into 4 large patties or 8 small patties.
In skillet over medium heat, melt margarine and brown patties on both sides. Blend cranberry sauce, water and bouillon; pour over patties. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until done.

title: shrimp salad louis
directions: *Can add 1 can (7 1/2 ounce) crab.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain 1/2 of pineapple juice from can.
Pour pineapple in mixing bowl.
Mix sugar and flour separately then toss together in pineapple.
Put in cheese and toss again.
Melt butter in 8 x 8 inch dish.
Pour in pineapple mixture and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serve warm or cold.
(Best right out of the oven!)

title: pumpkin streusel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugars.
Cut in margarine or butter until crumbly (use fingers if too stiff to work).
Stir in chopped nuts.
Reserve 1 cup of this crumb mixture.
Press remainder firmly in bottom and halfway up sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared dish and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake 55 minutes until golden brown.
Cool well before cutting into squares (should be well chilled).

title: baked cod
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put fish pieces into the dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Place carrots and potatoes between pieces and place dabs of margarine and pieces of potato over fish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Serve garnished with chopped parsley.
Yields 4 servings.
Approximate calories per serving: 330.

title: busha's cherry torte
directions: Mix margarine and sugar well.
Continue mixing, adding one egg at a time.
Add vanilla, then add flour and soda gradually.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of dough in cookie sheet.
Spoon cherries over dough, then spoon rest of dough on top (11 1/2 x 15-inch cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: spinach cups
directions: Trim bread crust.
Flatten bread slices with rolling pin. Cut slices into quarters.
Press into mini (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until bread cups are lightly browned.
Drain spinach.
Press between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Set aside.
Coat large skillet with cooking spray; add margarine. Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add onion and saute 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in spinach.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Combine cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Add spinach mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into bread cups (about 2 teaspoon per cup).
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield: 36 appetizers.

title: matzo brie
directions: In microwavable bowl, mix eggs and milk. Hold sheets of Matza under warm water, and crumble into bowl. Mix. Cook for 3 min. Cut and Enjoy.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven at 400° until brown.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook seasoned chicken until done.
Reserve broth.
Remove from bone.
Set meat aside.
Stir together soups, Veg-All and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Add chicken and pour into oblong casserole dish.

title: "philly" christmas cake
directions: Thoroughly blend softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Gradually add 2 cups sifted flour with baking powder.
Combine 1/4 cup flour with candied fruit and 1/2 cup chopped pecans; fold into batter.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan; sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Garnish with candied pineapple and cherries.

title: cream of mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Once mixed, add 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Mix together well.
Put in loaf pan and cook for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Layer top of meat loaf with mashed potatoes. Put back in oven for 10 minutes. Take 1/2 can mushroom soup and 1/4 cup milk and put in microwave for 1 minute. Put meat loaf and potatoes on plate.
Put cream of mushroom sauce over it.
Add your choice of veggies.
