title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in salted water until soft. Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Combine soup (undiluted) and rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Add broccoli.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° just long enough for cheese to melt.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Set aside.
In large bowl, break lettuce in bite size pieces, chop tomatoes in small pieces, chop green onions and chop avocado in small pieces.
Mix together.
Add 1 cup grated cheese, picante sauce, meat, Green Goddess, pinto beans and crushed Doritos.
Toss and serve.
Garlic bread is good with the salad.
You can substitute Catalina dressing in place of Green Goddess.

title: florida stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cut a thin slice from top of peppers.
Remove seeds.
Drop peppers into boiling water for 3 minutes only.
Drain and set upright in baking dish. Mix half the onions, all the beef and half the tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Stir in eggs, beaten with a fork. Mix in cooked rice; pile into peppers.
Top each pepper with a piece of bacon.
Put rest of tomatoes and chopped onions in dish around peppers.
Cover casserole.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake about 15 minutes to brown top.

title: peanut butter cups(tastes like reese's)
directions: Mix together in a bowl the peanut butter and powdered sugar. In a small saucepan, melt together the chocolate chips and margarine.
Roll peanut butter mixture into walnut size balls. Dip into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: lemon lush
directions: This dessert cake doesn't take four days to prepare but can easily be made ahead and served days later at optimum quality. Next time try using lemon or strawberry cake mix.
This cake improves with age as flavors blend.

title: danish (for weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix apricot spread, apricots, raisins, water and sugar; mix well.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits; spray cookie sheet with Pam spray.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture into each biscuit.
Bake until brown.
Exchanges:
1 bread and 1 fruit; 40 calories per serving.

title: flo's pizza pups
directions: Cover casserole and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Starting with the refried beans, layer as listed: beans, chicken, taco sauce, black olives and cheese, in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover.
Bake an additional 5 minutes until the cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Roll into balls the size of a marble.
Place on buttered cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Take flat glass and butter bottom. Dip into sugar and press on cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They brown easily.

title: yummy bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lay 1/2 slice Swiss cheese between each slice of bread. Mix mustard, butter and chives; spread on top of bread. Sprinkle chopped onions next. Then add the 8 slices of chopped raw bacon. Sprinkle with poppy seeds and bake 20 minutes. (Bake on baking sheet with sides.)

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and butter.
Pack in pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cook apples and drain.
Place them on crust.
Sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Mix egg, sour cream and sugar; drizzle over top of apples.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar; be beating well at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: camping snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, measure cereal, sugar, butterscotch pieces and peanuts.
Mix with hands, coarsely crumbling cereal.
Drizzle with margarine; toss.
Mix in M&M's.
Spoon into large Ziploc bag or into several individual bags.

title: murphy irish bread
directions: Mix in large bowl flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream in a small bowl margarine, sugar, egg and buttermilk.
Add wet ingredients gradually to dry to form a stiff batter.
Fold in raisins, currants and caraway seeds.
Turn into a greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Test with toothpick.
Turn out of pan immediately after removing from oven.

title: nan's pickles
directions: Refrigerate and shake often.
Best after two weeks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil (until it can not be stirred down). Then add the baking soda and vanilla.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Dice and brown celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Pour noodles over top and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: old fashioned filled cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Roll 1/8-inch on lightly floured surface and cut with a 2 3/4 inch cookie cutter.
Place heaping teaspoonful of filling on each cookie and top with another cookie round.
Crimp edges closed.

title: buck spread
directions: Place meat in food processor.
Grind.
Add pickles.
Grind again, add salt, pepper, mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix.
Spread on toasted bread for sandwich.
Serves 4.

title: mexican cornbread with meat
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.	Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan or 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bread is
golden
brown and tests done.
Serve with a salad and you have a complete meal.

title: easy chicken pot pie(turkey)
directions: Place flavor packet of Stove Top and butter in bowl.
Add hot water to partially melt margarine.
Add stuffing crumbs, stir gently to mix.
Combine soup and milk in 2-quart casserole dish. Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Spoon stuffing over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pea salad
directions: Put peas in strainer and run water over them.
Drain well, then mix in chopped onion, Cheddar cheese, parsley and pinch of salt and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble it into pea mix.
Mix salad dressing and sour cream together and toss with peas and bacon.
Chill and serve.

title: parmesan dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together.

title: apricot bread(one loaf)
directions: Soak apricots in warm water to cover.
Drain and cut up apricots.
Mix sugar and butter together thoroughly.
Stir in water and orange juice.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend in the nuts and apricots. Line bottom of greased loaf pan with paper.
Grease paper and pour in batter.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick thrust into the center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Take off paper immediately.
Let cool on rack.

title: easy ala king biscuit casserole
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan, over medium heat; stir in flour, then pour in broth and let thicken, stirring. Add chicken, peas, mushrooms, carrots, onion and bell pepper. Mix together and bring to a boil. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Pour chicken mixture into a 9X13 inch baking dish. Place refrigerated biscuits over top and bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until biscuits are done.

title: peperoni alle acciughe(pepper with anchovies)
directions: Wash anchovy fillets under running water for several minutes to rid them of their salt.
Bone them and cut into small pieces. Wash, dry and halve the peppers; remove ribs and seeds.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Cut into strips.
Place peppers on a serving dish and sprinkle with oregano, garlic, capers and anchovies.
Season with salt to taste.
Drizzle with oil.

title: apricot cheese ball
directions: Mix apricots with sugar, then combine with remaining ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
(It's best to mix together and put in refrigerator a while before trying to form ball.)

title: quick yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set mixture aside.
Combine butter, sugar and egg in a large bowl.
Beat well. Stir in yeast mixture. Gradually add flour, stirring well. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
(Mixture may be stored in the refrigerator for 2 days in an airtight container.)
To bake, spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: party salad
directions: Soften gelatin in lemon juice.
Add sugar, salt and boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Let cool.
Whip milk until stiff.
Fold or beat in mayonnaise; add gelatin mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together and press into large pie pan and bake.
Cool.

title: betty's chinese rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in a little oil.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Debone all meat and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in a large skillet.
Fry in a small amount of oil until done.
Drain any excess oil.
Mix onion, pepper, meat and steamed broccoli.
Serve with a little soy sauce or Worcestershire sauce.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Rice:
Soak wild rice overnight.
Rinse well.
Add 1 cup of wild rice to 3 cups boiling water in heavy saucepan (salt may be added).
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 to 50 minutes. Drain excess liquid.
For chewier texture, cook less time.
This yields 3 to 4 cups of cooked rice.

title: rum raisin cake
directions: Drain pineapple, pressing out 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice for cake.
Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, allspice and salt.
Beat in flour mixture in thirds alternately with reserved pineapple juice and rum.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with buttermilk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, one at a time, in deep fat fryer.

title: boiled dressing for cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil and slowly pour the eggs which have been well beaten.
Add dry ingredients.
Return to heat and cook until thick.

title: jam cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks. Put spices in flour.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add jam, then beaten egg whites.
Beat the 2 egg whites; add sugar and put on (between) layers.

title: frozen lemon pudding(servings:  4)
directions: Mix in bowl egg yolk, sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff; gradually whip in 2 tablespoons sugar. Fold egg white mixture into egg yolk mixture.
Whip milk in cold bowl until fluffy.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice and whip until stiff.
Fold into egg mixture.
Put into ice tray.
Sprinkle over top 1 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze in ice tray.
Do not stir.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In 5-quart pot, fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper just until there is no pink.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer at least 2 hours, stirring as necessary.
Add any additional spices to taste while simmering.
Makes 4 quarts of sauce.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake at
for 1 hour in greased tube pan.
Remove from pan; cool and serve.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together.
Mix soda, extract and beaten egg with buttermilk.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with flour.
If dough seems too soft to roll, add a little more flour.
Roll to desired thinness, cut, place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Peel and slice green tomatoes.
Make batter of Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Dip tomatoes in batter, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot cooking oil until brown.

title: quick-baked pasta family style
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until the meat is tender and then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheese for topping and the pasta.
Simmer.
Add 3/4 pound pasta (small pasta tubes) to the boiling water.
Cook until barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix with the sauce.
Pour all into a 3-quart glass baking dish and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until all is bubbly hot. Great for freezer, refrigerator or microwave.
Serves 6.

title: garden patch coleslaw
directions: Rinse frozen peas under running cold water just until thawed, about 1/2 minute.
Drain and place in bowl.
Drizzle dressing over peas; toss until coated.
In large serving dish, mix peas and coleslaw.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven over medium heat; remove and set aside.
Reserve 3 1/2 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven, adding vegetable oil if necessary.
Saute green pepper and onion in reserved drippings until onion is tender.
Add sausages and marinara sauce; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hard rolls or over your favorite hot cooked pasta.
Sprinkle each serving with grated Romano cheese.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets. Cream together butter, brown sugar and white sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition, then stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually stir into creamed mixture. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop dough into rounded spoonfuls onto cookie sheets. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown. Allow cookies to cool for 5 minutes.

title: po-man's lasagna
directions: Cook enough rigatoni pasta for your family.
Drain and put in a large casserole dish.
Combine sauce ingredients and add to pasta.
Top with more grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and chill.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, carrots, macaroni, peas, onion, ham and eggs. Combine mayonnaise, dill weed and salt.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: rhine burgers
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with salt, caraway seed and pepper; shape into 8 patties, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place 2 tablespoonfuls sauerkraut on each of 4 patties; top with remaining patties.
Wrap 2 slices bacon around each; fasten with moistened wooden picks.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 6 minutes on each side or until bacon is crisp.
Serve each between 2 slices buttered pumpernickel.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender and drain.
Combine beans, sour cream, sugar, salt and pepper.
In a separate boiler simmer oleo, flour and onion until thick.
Add to bean mixture and place in casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top and sprinkle corn flakes on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.
Yield 3 quarts. Makes a lot, good to freeze.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients. Let partially set, then beat with egg beater.

title: easy baked fish
directions: In a baking dish, arrange fish portions.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and basil.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place tomato slice on each portion.
Sprinkle with green onions and cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted and mixture is hot.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside. Combine milk, egg and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry until brown in a deep fryer at 375°.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple with juice.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let stand several hours.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth and creamy. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: orange roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large mixing bowl.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll each in powdered sugar.
Chill.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two unbaked crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Skin and debone.
Cut in small pieces.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Be sure to use juice in pineapple.
If it isn't moist enough, add more dressing, 1 tablespoon at a time.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and continue to beat until light. Add vanilla.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: Oil in wok.
Add beef and garlic and cook.
Stir 2 minutes. Push to one side of skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook.
Stir 1 minute.
Add pepper strips, broth, pepper and salt.
Stir until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add scallions.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring until well blended. Pour in two slightly greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about an hour.
While bread is baking, prepare the following sauce.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Clean and peel shrimp.
Drain crabmeat (pick out shells if you buy crabmeat in a container).
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Spread evenly into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until shrimp are pink and casserole is brown on top.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken at 425°, covered, for 15 minutes.
Drain. Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour over chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: dill crackers
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a pot with a lid.
Shake to mix. Then pour oil over mix.
Stir thoroughly with a large spoon. Repeat the stirring every 5 to 10 minutes for 45 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Scald milk with the oleo in it.
Mix the salt, sugar, eggs and cherries.
Add the bread crumbs and mix well.
Pour the milk-oleo mixture over the bread mixture and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: quick chocolate-caramel cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.

When cake is done, poke holes all over the top (about the size of a ball point pen). Heat hot fudge and spread over the top of the cake while it is still hot. Heat caramel and spread over the top. Let cool completely on counter or put in fridge. Top with whipped cream when ready to serve. Sprinkle candy bits on top. Store any leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Place a vanilla wafer in each paper-lined cup of a muffin pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers, filling cup full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Leave in muffin pan; cover and chill overnight.

title: honey spice banana cake
directions: Make batter as directed, except stir 1/8 teaspoon soda into mix before adding liquid and eggs.
Use only 3/4 cup water and add 1 cup mashed bananas (2 to 3 bananas).
If desired, fold 1/3 cup nuts into batter.
Pour into prepared oblong or layer pans.
Bake as directed.
Frost with Banana-Nut Frosting.

title: lattice chicken bake
directions: Layer ingredients, except cheese and onion rings, into large, glass baking dish.
Place dough on top to form a lattice effect. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425° or until brown.
Place cheese and onion rings on top and bake 3 to 5 minutes more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a shaker and shake well.
Can be stored in refrigerator.
Delicious on spareribs, short ribs and chicken.

title: famous southern biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside. Add flour, sugar, oil and buttermilk. Mix, then add yeast and water mixture. Work and knead together. Cover and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: killer tacos
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Salt to taste.
Add 8 ounces of Pace picante sauce; simmer.
Shred lettuce and cheese into separate bowls.

title: cookies in a crust
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl until foamy.
Add sugar, flour and brown sugar; mix well.
Mix in very soft butter.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into butter flavored pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together all ingredients.
Warm over medium heat.
Good served with mashed potatoes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Place milk, chocolate, butter, eggs and sugar in an electric blender and blend for 15 seconds. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan and sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and store any leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for one hour on a rack or broiler pan.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine chocolate chips and half and half in heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth stirring frequently.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm.
Yield 2 cups.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.
Heat carefully to prevent burning.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in a little butter.
Add corn, tomatoes and cooked noodles.
Season to taste.
Put in buttered casserole dish and put buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Brown in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruited squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Measure 1 cup and fold into whipped topping.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Place fruit over creamy layer, then spoon remaining gelatin over fruit.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Place cut up bacon in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until crispy.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Add onion, green pepper and celery to bacon drippings. Micro on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover with a tight lid or plastic wrap.
Micro on High for 5 to 6 minutes until bubbly. Stir and then micro on Medium for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat and pour into greased dish or pan. Put in refrigerator until set.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour diluted can of cream of chicken soup over rice.
Stir well.
Place salted and peppered chicken breast over rice.
Pour can of diluted cream of mushroom soup over chicken breasts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour and brown in small amount of oil. May cook in electric skillet.
Add water (2 cups only).
Add seasonings to taste.
Cook over low heat (200° to 225°) in electric skillet until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes, onions and 1 cup of water, if needed.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are done, approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: In blender,
put egg, onion, potatoes and salt.
Do not cover; liquify.
With rubber spatula, push potatoes down into blending mixture.
As
soon as mixed, shut off.
Stir in matzo meal to make desired consistency.
Drop by spoonfuls into 1/2 inch hot cooking
oil
and
fry until golden brown.	Drain on paper.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce.

title: tamale squares
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and margarine; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper, cook until tender.
Reserve 1/3 cup Cheez Whiz and 1/2 cup tomato.
Stir in remaining Cheez Whiz, tomato and chili powder.
Spoon meat mixture over batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with reserved Cheez Whiz and tomato; continue baking 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Cover bottom of large frying pan with a thin coating of bacon grease.
Place apples in pan. Sprinkle on the sugar.
Add the water.
Place top on pan and cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: company casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Set oven at 350°.
Boil noodles 10 minutes; drain.
Brown hamburger in 1 tablespoon of butter. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
In a casserole, spread half of the noodles in the bottom and top with half the cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Pat ground beef mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato-peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Boil the potato until well done.
Mash while hot. Add powdered sugar slowly, small amounts at a time, until it is in a dough stage. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread evenly with chunky peanut butter and roll up.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Slice into 1/4-inch or 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve cold.

title: laura's broccoli salad
directions: Finely chop heads of broccoli (not stems).
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, white vinegar and sugar together and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix broccoli, bacon and cheese.
Toss with mayonnaise and vinegar dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat
oven to
Grease,
then
line
with
wax paper, 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Sift into large Mixmaster Mixer bowl sifted flour, granulated sugar, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar, shortening, chocolate,
3/4 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 30 seconds at No. 1 to moisten flour; then 2 minutes at No. 4. Add
remaining milk and eggs.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes longer; pour into pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes; cool.

title: potato pot
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden and slightly crispy on edges.

title: the ultimate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before cutting.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Boil together vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage, onions and peppers.
Put in jar in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: mother's carrot cake
directions: Add oil, white sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients except carrots.
Mix well and add 3 cups grated carrots.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers or 1 loaf.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll in waxed paper and put in refrigerator overnight. Cut and bake at 350°.

title: million dollar chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk in large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat.
Bring to rolling boil and cook for 6 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Chill until set.
Score and eat.

title: ranch style biscuits
directions: Mix together 1 package of yeast and 1/2 cup of lukewarm water; set aside. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the oil and buttermilk to other liquids; stir together before mixing with dry ingredients.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Roll out and cut before cooking for 20 to 25 minutes at 425° on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Mix flour, salt, water, eggs and sesame seed.
Beat together until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter and drop in hot oil.
Oil should cover chicken. Cook each piece about 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown. Drain.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly; cool 5 minutes.
Add choice of the peanut butter or chocolate chips and choice of oats or coconut.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients, starting with the lettuce. Continue until all ingredients are used (the more layers the better).
Spread the mayonnaise over top of salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix together eggs, sugar, salad oil and vanilla.
Sift together and mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and zucchini.
Combine the two mixtures thoroughly.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: cheese biscuits(like the ones served at red lobster)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add grated cheese, stir, then add milk.
Mix together well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Boil pudding, sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Beat in butter until mixture becomes thick and glossy.
Pour into greased pan.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and flour. Knead the dough until smooth, adding more flour (up to 1 cup) if dough is sticky.
Divide dough into walnut-size pieces.
Each child rolls his ball into a 12 to 14-inch rope and shape.
Brush them with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Let rest on cookie sheet, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour,
salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar together twice.
Then
put
juice
and
finely chopped rind of orange in cup
and
add
shortening
and fill remainder of cup with boiling water
to
3/4 full.
Add juice and beaten egg to dry ingredients.
Also add nuts and cranberries (cut in half). Makes two small loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potato mixture and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: I used hot sausage and regular Ro-Tel, and it is pretty spicy. You can adjust the heat with the tomatoes and sausage.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean and remove stems carefully.
Stuff cavity with a walnut-size ball of sausage.
Put under broiler 15 to 20 minutes.
So easy and so good.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cook all together.
Place in pie crust of your choice.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: tenderloin tips in beer
directions: Season tips with salt and pepper and shake in bag containing the flour.
Pour a thin film of oil in skillet and saute the onion, leek, shallot and garlic until tender.
Remove the saute mixture with a slotted spoon and place in a casserole dish.
In the same skillet, brown meat on all sides, adding more oil as needed.
You may have to do this in several batches.
Add the browned meat to casserole.
Pour half the can of beer into the skillet; mix with pan juices, scraping sides and bottom of pan. Pour this over meat in casserole; add remaining beer, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours on top of stove.
Dish is done when meat is tender.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours or more.

title: the marching pride
directions: Blend together wonderful winds, boisterous brass, dynamic drumline, bodacious band front and perfect pit.
Stir with 2 dedicated drum majors.
Sprinkle in generously 1 bunch of caring chaperones.
Fold in 1 superb staff and top it all with 1 terrific, enthusiastic band director.
Shake with an attitude of excellence and bake well on West Allegheny's parking lot and practice field.
Excellent served at half-time on football fields. Serves thousands.

title: ham and cheese salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ham and cheese with the green onions and parsley.
In a small bowl, whisk the vinegar, mustard, salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Gradually whisk in the olive oil in a thin stream.
Pour the dressing over the ham and cheese and toss well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 8 (4 cup) servings.

title: strudel coffee cake
directions: Dissolve
yeast and sugar in warm milk.
Mix all ingredients together
and
let
rise.
When double in bulk, divide into 2 parts.
Roll
out
but
not too thin.
Rub melted oleo over
the rolled
out
dough.
Mix
together the brown sugar, pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the mixture over each 1/2 of
rolled out
dough.
Roll
up
like
jelly roll.
Place on greased cookie sheet, let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30
minutes
or until brown.
When cool, drizzle with powdered sugar icing and garnish with cherry halves.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter, sugar and egg.
Mix & sift flour & soda & add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 45 minutes in a 375 degree oven.

title: coco (rabbit) in wine marinade
directions: Place rabbit in crock or glass dish.
Mix wine, spices, onion and enough vinegar to cover. Marinate for two days in refrigerator.
Save marinade.

title: grandma's choc-oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate and walnuts; mix well. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Remove to cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: 30 day cole slaw
directions: Mix last five ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over cabbage-pepper-onion-sugar.
Do not stir.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours.
Then stir.
Will last up to 30 days in refrigerator.

title: calico vegetable relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: holiday magic yams
directions: Drain yams.
Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup peach juice; set aside.
In 11-inch skillet, heat remaining juice, liquid brown sugar, cranberry sauce, cinnamon and butter.
When butter is melted, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened.
Add yams, cover skillet and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in peaches and cook 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: normandy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and oil in skillet and saute apples with cinnamon, sugar, ginger, thyme and cloves about 5 minutes or until limp, stirring occasionally.
Place apples in bottom of a baking dish and set aside.

title: great pie crust
directions: Mix shortening with salt and boiling water, whip until fluffy. Stir in 3 cups flour until dough forms a ball.
Sprinkle extra flour on the dough until not sticky.
Roll and edge pie crust. Prick with fork, bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 2 large pie crusts.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix brown sugar and juice in large saucepan or percolator. Stud orange wedge with cloves and add to mixture.
Put other spices in percolator basket and perk or tie in cheesecloth and add to pan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer at least 10 minutes. Remove spices.
Serve warm with orange slices.

title: seven vegetable medley
directions: Combine all but 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the onions.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered.
Arrange cheese and onions on top and bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: potato salad
directions: Add the sugar and salt to vinegar; pour over diced potatoes. Allow to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and salad dressing; toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips at low heat.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts. Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Serve warm over tortilla chips, vegetables or baked potatoes. Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, chicken, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and jalapeno peppers.
Top half of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture, spreading evenly to within one-inch of edge.
Moisten edges of tortillas with water; fold over, pressing edges to seal. On 2 large baking sheets, arrange filled tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Top with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 8 quesadillas.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with hand mixer.
Use graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: hazel's famous low country hot dog chili
directions: First brown and drain ground beef.
Next, add Lipton onion soup mix; mix well.
Chop onion and bell pepper, then add to beef mixture.
Now add ketchup and continue stirring to avoid sticking. At this point, you can add crushed tomatoes according to taste.

title: mimosa fiddlehead greens salad
directions: In heavy 2 to 3-quart saucepan, bring to boil 3/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Drop in fiddleheads.
Reduce heat to simmer (low) and partially cover the pan.
Simmer for 2 minutes until they are barely tender and show only slight resistance when pierced with point of a skewer or small knife.
Drain in colander and run cold water over them to set their color and stop their cooking.
Then spread on paper towels and pat dry.
Place chopped garlic in large salad bowl and pour in salad oil and vinegar.

title: chile-cheese loaf
directions: Allow dough to thaw at room temperature.
On lightly floured board, roll dough out to 14 x 12-inch rectangle.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with cheese and chiles.
Beginning from long side, tightly roll dough up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down on baking sheet, pinching ends together to form oval.
With sharp knife or scissors, cut slashes in dough at 1-inch intervals.
Brush dough with remaining butter.
Allow to rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and allow to cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Make cake in 9 x 12-inch sheet pan.
Cool.
Cut into cubes. Make pudding.
Set 5 minutes.
Break up candy bars in baggie with rolling pin.
Layer in pedestal bowl: 1/2 cubed cake, 1/2 c. Kahula, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 candy bars and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat, ending up with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candy bars on top.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and butter. Beat 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: g.i.  slaw
directions: Combine carrots and raisins.
Mix with your favorite slaw dressing.

title: tortilla sandwiches
directions: Fry tortillas
in small amount of oil for a few seconds to soften.
Place 1/2 slice of Jack cheese on half the tortilla. Using tongs or fork, fold over.
Fry until crisp.
Turn and crisp the other side. As cheese melts, it seals the sandwich.
Makes 12 sandwiches or 6 servings.

title: broccoli-bacon salad
directions: Delicious and easy to prepare!

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Lightly grease a casserole pan.
Cook grits in salted water until smooth and creamy.
Stir in margarine, cheeses and Worcestershire sauce.
Place into prepared casserole and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is slightly brown.
Do not overcook.
Yields 8 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate dough on crescent rolls.
Roll 1 piece apple in dough spiral and lay in 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Separate them apart in pan 3-inches or so.
Heat margarine, orange juice and sugar to a boil. Sprinkle allspice and cinnamon over the rolls, after pouring orange juice over the rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's crock-pot beans 'n tomatoes
directions: Put cleaned and washed beans and 2 quarts water in a large pan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 1 to 3 hours.
While beans soak, warm 1 quart water in crock.
Put on low setting.
Drain beans and rinse with hot water; add to crock-pot.
Stir in ginger.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours (low 7 to 8 hours) or until beans are tender.
One hour before serving, add tomatoes and salt.
Crumbled bacon or diced ham can also be added for flavor.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: To make cookie crust for bars:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no stick spray.
Mix flour, 2 sticks butter and 1/2 cup sugar until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat out cookie dough on pizza pan and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Should be done but not crisp.
Let cool.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cream cheese (more cream cheese may be used if desired) and vanilla; spread over crust.
Place fruit around until covered.
Fruit may be thinly sliced and placed in circles around top of cream cheese.
Apples, oranges, bananas, kiwi, peaches, pineapple and cherries or combinations can be used.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of prepared batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Layer apples and crust (don't do bottom crust; stays doughy). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef-drain.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Simmer; then let meat mixture cool.
Tear lettuce to bite size.
Combine with beans, cheese, onion, & taco meat.
Crush chips and add to mixture. Finally, add dressing and tomato wedges and gently mix.

title: blueberry cake(peaches or apples)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening; combine 1/2 cup milk with 2 scant tablespoons vinegar mixed to make sour milk.
Add 1 egg and then milk and mix well.
Spread thin in a large flat cake pan and cover well with fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for about 15 minutes.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Brown rice and onion in the margarine in a skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until brown (about 15 to 20 minutes). Add consomme and mushrooms.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover; continue baking for an additional 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal rocks
directions: Better with 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork and chicken
until
done
and
pull meat from bones. Cut into small pieces.
Mix meat and other ingredients and cook slowly for	several
hours.
Must remember to stir to keep from sticking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and shred chicken (desired amount). For white sauce use equal amount of butter and flour. (example: 2 tbsp. melted mutter with 2 tbsp. flour). Stir together in large skillet (don't let it get too brown) add basil, parsley, garlic, pepper, white wine, and then grated Parmesan cheese. Boil spiral noodles, add chicken and peas to sauce in skillet. Put noodles in casserole dish, add sauce and stir together. Add a little Parmesan and Cheddar cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: russian fluff
directions: Remove meat and vegetables from pan.
Skim off fat; strain and measure broth.
Add water to make 2 cups of liquid for every 3 pounds of pot roast.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into oblong pan or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for oblong pan or at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes for tube pan.

title: goodwiches
directions: Mayonnaise tortillas.
Place small amounts of each ingredient on tortillas, adding beef slices last.
Close one end, fold, then roll up.
(Only small amounts are needed, or it can't be rolled up very well.)

title: the best spinach salad dressing
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill thoroughly and stir before using. Makes 1-1/2 cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms(a great holiday appetizer)
directions: Wash mushrooms and pop off stems.
Melt butter in a large skillet with lid.
Make a small mound of sausage (room temperature) in cap.
Use your fingers and push in.
Do not break cap.
Cover bottom of skillet with mushroom caps, sausage side up. Cover and cook until caps shrink and sausage cooks, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm, immediately.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with can milk. Mix well and add flavoring. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Place in COLD oven and turn oven to 325°. Bake 1 hour 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Do not open oven door while baking. Remove from pan immediately.

title: don's bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Place in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, evaporated milk, 2 cups milk, vanilla, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove and make meringue.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Cover pudding with meringue and rebake for 3 or 4 minutes until meringue is golden.
Serves 12.

title: pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 (8 1/2-inch) loaf pans. Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin. Into mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients. Make a well in center. Add pumpkin mixture. Blend just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake 1 hour.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison into strips and set aside.
Mix together the rest of ingredients.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread rice and top with chicken. Sprinkle complete package of onion soup over top and add water. Put pats of butter on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour (or until chicken is done).

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix and cool.
Leave in pan; poke holes in cake. Mix Jell-O and pour over cake.
Ice cake with Cool Whip and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, cinnamon, eggs, and sugar in bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13 in baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts over pumpkin.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan. Beat eggs, flour, milk and salt.
(Can use a blender.)
Pour beaten ingredients into hot butter.
Put in oven preheated to 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 10 minutes more. After removing from oven, spread with strawberry jam.
Drizzle a little lemon juice and powdered sugar over this.

title: lasagna
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper and brown.
Add garlic, onion and pepper. Simmer slowly, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce; cover and simmer. Pour 1/3 of meat sauce into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with strips of lasagna noodles.
Add Mozzarella, Cheddar and spoonfuls of cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour in graham cracker crust. Chill several hours before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients except shrimp.
Mix well.
Add shrimp.

title: chili-bean-soup
directions: Brown ground beef quickly over medium-high heat, stirring with potato masher.
Drain well; remove from heat and put in bowl.
In same skillet, brown onion slightly.
Add meat,
kidney beans and tomato soup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: louisiana pecan pork
directions: Slice pork into 1-inch pieces; rinse well.
Combine flour, seasoned salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Roll moist meat in flour mixture; set aside.

title: healthful morning muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 medium muffin pan or line with paper baking cups.
Combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat in oil and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Stew chicken breast, adding celery, onion, salt and pepper if desired.
Cube meat and mix with sour cream and soup.
Put mixture in a 2 quart casserole.
Mix together stuffing mix, butter and broth.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with cranberry sauce and a salad for lunch or add a vegetable for dinner.

title: onion-noodleburger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Turn down heat; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, or until noodles are done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a casserole dish.
Fry together ground beef, onion and pepper.
In a small amount of water, cook cabbage until tender.
Layer meat mixture and cabbage in casserole.
Melt butter; stir in flour; cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and thick.
Add Jack cheese and pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: ma and pa green beans
directions: Fill very large pot with ingredients.
Fill with water just above ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil, then uncover and simmer until green beans darken and soften (about an hour or so)!

title: vegetable-herb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll bread dough into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch rectangle.
Place in jelly roll pan.
With fingertips, firmly press into dough at 1-inch intervals.
Arrange tomato slices, fresh sage leaves and onion wedges on top of bread dough. Sprinkle with oil over vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until browned and crisp.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples sugar and vinegar in a large container.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours, then bring to a boil.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Have shell ready.
Use enough apples to fill 1 pie shell.
Put butter on top, then sprinkle allspice over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until thickened.
Make more pies with unused apples or put in freezer bags and freeze for later use.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to spreading consistency.
Split rolls.
Spread each half with mixture.
Place a slice of ham and a slice of cheese on the bottom half of the rolls.
Replace the top of the rolls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-20 minutes.
Serve warm. Suitable for freezing.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain. Melt oleo; add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Add raisins to this mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
May add a top crust before baking.

title: butterscotch pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, oleo, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: green beans scandia
directions: Heat green beans in their own liquid.
Meanwhile, melt butter/margarine in skillet.
Add tarragon and chives and simmer gently for two minutes.
Turn off heat and stir in sour cream. Combine with drained hot green beans and serve immediately.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown neck bones in a large pot with 2 tablespoons salad oil. Add the water and cook for 2 hours.
(After 2 hours, make sure there are at least 1 1/2 cans of water left.)
Add the crushed blended tomatoes, tomato paste and soda.
Cook for 25 minutes in covered pot.
Stir constantly.
Add the spices and onions.
Add the meats that have been browned in oven for about 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Add wine and continue to cook in covered pot for at least 15 minutes.
Stir constantly to avoid sauce burning to bottom of the pan.
Serves a crowd.

title: cinnamon potpourri ornaments
directions: Combine applesauce and gelatin in a small saucepan.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until simmering.
Remove from heat.

title: corn relish
directions: Scrape the corn from the cob.
Mix the corn kernels with the remaining ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into warm sterilized jars and cover.

title: vegie dip
directions: Boil water; add and dissolve the bouillon cubes.
Combine with mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate. Serve with vegies or as chip dip.

title: beef and cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
In large pot, add all ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.

title: vegetarian main dish-broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, drain.
Blend baking mix, milk, eggs, salt and onion with mixer until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Bake at 325 until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about an hour.
Finished dish resembles a souffle.

title: mom's cookies
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients.
In another bowl put and mix all wet ingredients.
After mixed well, pat together dry and wet, then add oats, nuts, raisins and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts; mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill at least two hours. Serve fat-free crackers or raw vegetables.
You may get a round loaf of bakery bread and cut out the top as you would a pumpkin. Remove enough bread to make room for the dip.
Cut the removed bread into large cubes and serve with the fat-free crackers.
Makes 12 generous servings of 1/3 cup each.
One serving equals 1/4 V and 45 optional cal.

title: yogurt cake cop out
directions: Mix gelatin using only 1 c. of boiling water.
Pierce cake all over with large meat fork or skewer.
Pour gelatin mixture into holes very slowly.
Allow to set up.
Blend the yogurt with the Cool Whip and frost the cake. Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook salad macaroni per directions on package.
Let cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, add onions to fat and brown slightly.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to bacon fat, water and vinegar; boil for at least 1 minute or until thick.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt Parkay.
Add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then add nuts and chocolate chips.
Cook in 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: peach jam
directions: Peel peaches and cut in half.
Remove pits.
Put peaches, whole oranges and whole lemons through a food processor, using a coarse blade.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add cream cheese and marshmallows. Chill until slightly thickened. Add whipped topping, mayonnaise, grated carrots and drained pineapple. Chill until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brush with white of egg.
Bake slow for 2 hours.

title: strawberry freeze pie
directions: Dice approximately 1 pint of strawberries.
Crush cookies and sift through strainer.
Re-crush leftovers and sift until all cookies sift.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip; add diced strawberries. Mix well.
Pour mix into pie crust.
Spoon cookie crumbs over top and even out with fork.
Garnish with remaining strawberries and freeze.

title: italian stallion sandwich
directions: Simmer sausage in water until done.
Melt butter in skillet. Saute onion, pepper, mushrooms and garlic until tender (5 to 7 minutes).
Split rolls.
Divide vegetable mixture among rolls. Split cooked sausage and place on top of vegetables.
Pour 1/3 cup sauce on each sandwich.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano and paprika.
Heat under broiler until cheese melts and begins to brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Garnish with pickles and parsley.

title: buttermilk pecan pralines
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, buttermilk and soda until it reaches soft ball stage.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until thick enough to drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper (brown onion and pepper separate from beef).
Mix other ingredients; simmer then add beef, onion and pepper.
Simmer for several hours to improve flavor. Add kidney beans last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serves 75.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix well in blender and serve.
Keep chilled.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast and mix. Place desired amount of dough on floured surface.
Pat out and cut with biscuit cutter or shape dough into rolls.
Mixture can be stored in covered container in refrigerator for several days. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cook marshmallows, Coca-Cola, cocoa, Wesson oil and butter together until the marshmallows are melted, stirring frequently. Set aside to cool.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add mixture to sifted ingredients and beat.
Add mixture to Coca-Cola mixture.
Bake in oblong 12 x 10-inch pan at 350° for almost 40 minutes.

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Put sugar, milk and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture cannot be stirred down.
Put lid on; cook 1 minute over medium heat.
Remove and add 1 stick butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir.
Frost cake.

title: mocha logs
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and coffee. Stir in oats and nuts.
Shape small pieces into logs about 2 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
Roll lightly in confectioners sugar and then in chocolate sprinkles.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into topping.
Add fruit.
Blend.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Place in refrigerator 45 minutes before cutting.

title: golden banana fritters
directions: Peel bananas and cut in pieces, roll in well beaten egg and flour them in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot shortening until golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk; heat thoroughly.
Garnish, if desired, with shredded cheese, cooked diced ham or bacon.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Boil 5 or 6 minutes until thick.
Mix in 1 box strawberry jello and 2 drops red food coloring; cool.
Place strawberries in pie crust.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle sugar, strawberry jello and marshmallows on top. Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: florida pie
directions: Mix in large bowl, lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk, crushed pineapple, bananas, mandarin oranges, chopped walnuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well, then place in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: stouffer's spinach souffle
directions: Butter a 10-inch casserole dish and put frozen spinach on bottom to thaw.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over spinach. Crush Ritz crackers and mix with margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain grease.
Cut up potatoes into small chunks; place in large pot with hamburger, onion and enough water to cover potatoes.
Add chili powder. Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add green peppers, chili beans and corn and cook about 20 more minutes.
We always eat it with buttered bread.

title: golden eagle pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Sprinkle nut meats in unbaked pie shell and filling.
Bake in moderate oven for about 55 minutes.

title: stuffed beets
directions: Boil baby beets until tender, peel.
Cut off tops.
Scoop out a bit of center.
Fill hole with cream cheese flavored with horseradish. Serve cold.

title: pizza eggs
directions: In a microwave-safe 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish, cook margarine, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine eggs, milk, mushrooms, salt, Italian seasoning and pepper; pour into baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until eggs are almost set, pushing cooked portions to center of dish several times during cooking.
Pour pizza sauce over eggs. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese starts to melt.
Garnish with sliced olives and cilantro, if desired.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Save juice.
Add juice to jello, stir in water.
Heat to boiling.
Remove and blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill to thicken slightly.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate to set mold.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together with salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick butter; pour over 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, sugar and 2 cups of milk about 1/2 hour.
Add the other 2 cups of milk, the egg yolks and the vanilla.
Finish cooking for another 1/2 hour.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold in pudding after it is cooked.

title: crock-pot beef
directions: Cut beef into pieces and brown.
Slice onion and dice carrots and celery.
Slice pepper into thin strips.
Place these into bottom of crock-pot.
Sprinkle the beef pieces with pepper, minced garlic and onion soup mix.
Mix the steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl with about 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Pour this over the meat.
Cook for 7 to 9 hours on low heat.
When done remove meat and vegetables and thicken with cornstarch or flour mixture.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 9 g, protein 19 g, fat 18 g, calories 277.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Press wafers in bottom of dish.
Add pineapple.
Mix together the vanilla, eggs, butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over pineapple.
Add the other can of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Crumble more vanilla wafers over top.
Add pecans, if desired.

title: seasoned pepper
directions: Place all ingredients in a pint jar and seal. Shake until mixture is completely blended.
Yields about 1 1/3 cups of seasoning.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Spread in a greased 11 x 7-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn.
Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: warm crab dip
directions: Shred crab meat into small pieces.
Blend in a small bowl, softened cream cheese with Worcestershire sauce, half and half, shredded crab meat, onion and horseradish sauce.
Mix lightly, but well.
Butter small baking dish and fill with crab mixture. Sprinkle with almonds and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn chowder
directions: Blend together corn, mushroom soup and evaporated milk and water.
Heat over medium heat and top with sauteed onions.
If you like, a few cooked carrots may be added for color.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook onion with cabbage in salt water.
Pour leftover gravy or bacon drippings into mixture.
Heat vinegar, plus sugar.
Add to mixture.
Add oatmeal for thickening.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with food coloring.
Cool in cold water.
Drain well.
Pour oil over noodles.
Toss well.
Blend in blender the remaining ingredients.
Pour over noodles and chill. For color and taste, add chopped green pepper, radish, celery, tomatoes, etc.
Stir occasionally.
May be made a couple of days in advance for full flavor.
Can be kept in refrigerator for a week.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook mushrooms, onion and butter in skillet until onions are tender; remove. In same skillet, brown beef lightly on both sides. Reserve 1/3 cup bouillon; add remaining bouillon, catsup, garlic and salt to skillet. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Blend reserved 1/3 cup bouillon with flour; stir into skillet. Add mushrooms and onion. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute. Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; boil for two minutes.
Line cookie sheets with graham crackers (tightly).
Add nuts to boiling mixture.
Spoon mixture on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut on cracker lines.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and cream cheese with a mixer on low until smooth. Add Cool Whip.
Mix together with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle crushed Oreos on top.
If desired, make layers of pudding, then crushed cookies, then pudding and top with cookies.

title: stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, onion and mushrooms in skillet. Brown.
Add seasonings and soup.
Cook
1/2 hour before serving. Add sour cream.
Heat (but do not bring to a boil) and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Blend in remaining dry ingredients.
Drop dough by a teaspoon on a cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake mix.
Follow directions on box and pour into greased baking pan (11 x 13-inch).

title: curried crab soup
directions: Add the chicken broth to the pepper pot soup and evaporated milk.
Season with curry and salt.
Heat but do not boil.
Just before serving, stir in the crab meat which has been picked over. Reheat to the steam stage.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet; saute onion in hot fat until golden brown.
Soak crumbs in water and cream; add meats, egg, onion and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Shape into very small balls.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodle package; set aside.

title: italian anise cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening, eggs and anise. Mix well.
Works best using hands.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until brown on bottom.

title: hamburger stew
directions: *Could be 1 cup of either macaroni or noodles.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Mix in peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix thoroughly.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate over hot water; spread over cracker mixture.
Cool.
Cut.

title: cucumbers and onions in vinegar
directions: Slice in bowl the cucumber and onion.
Combine vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Pour over the sliced cucumber and onion.
Let set 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Roll roast in flour and brown with a little oil in Dutch oven (large cooking pot). Add all other ingredients, except gingersnaps, and simmer 3 to 4 hours or all day in crock-pot. Add gingersnaps to thicken gravy. Meat will shred it is so tender.

title: joe's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients!
Mix well and place in 13 x 9-inch lightly greased dish.
Put catsup on top of meat loaf.
Bake until done on 350°.

title: delicious apple pie
directions: In a small bowl, mix water and cornstarch until dissolved.
Add egg, cream, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place apples in a large bowl; pour cream mixture over and stir to coat.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with the bottom pastry.
Pour apple mixture into crust; dot with butter.
Top with remaining pastry; flute edges and cut slits in top.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth and vegetables in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in chicken soup, chicken and pepper.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine flour, milk and butter; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Cook at medium heat until it boils.
Set aside to cool.

title: pull apart pizza bread
directions: Place biscuits in a well greased 9 by 9-inch square baking dish.
Spray biscuits with olive oil spray.
Sprinkle on Italian seasoning.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Pull apart to serve.

title: gwen's vegetarian soup
directions: Soak all dried beans except lentils and split peas overnight. Cook beans in about 4 cups water for about 1 hour.
(Not the lentils and split peas.)
If beans seem hard, cook awhile longer. Add lentils and split peas.

Simmer for 20 minutes. Add canned tomatoes, celery, carrots and onions and all spices and herbs. Simmer for 30 minutes. Add more water if too thick. Add potatoes and turnips (if adding). Simmer for 15 minutes. Add frozen corn and green beans. Simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni like box says.
Mix mayo and tuna, then add English peas.
Mix with macaroni.

title: southwestern potato salad
directions: With spatula, combine mayonnaise and mustard with ingredients through salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Mix gently but well. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the vanilla and lemon juice.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla and lemon juice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Grease or spray Pam on a 9 x 13-inch pan (or two 8 x 8-inch pans).
Pour half of batter into pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, melt butter, milk and caramels together.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour caramel mix over cake.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Pour other half of cake batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, may dust cake with confectioners sugar or each piece with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: Fry pork in a pan with sprinkled soy sauce.
Add cut up onions and celery.
Simmer until well cooked (makes its own juice; do not add water).
When cooked, thicken with 1/4 to 1/2 cup soy sauce and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add drained bean sprouts.
Serve over noodles, hamburger rolls, rice or potatoes.

title: raisin vanilla drops
directions: Boil raisins in uncovered pan until water is mostly absorbed. Cool 30 minutes.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown well on both sides.
Add cooking sherry, marmalade and bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender, spooning sauce over chicken occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: mary's drink
directions: Grate or grind oranges and lemons.
Cover with quart of boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Strain into cloth and squeeze. Dissolve sugar and citric acid in cold water.
Mix strained juice with this solution.
Add enough water to make a gallon.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy, then add sugar and salt.
Stir in oleo, syrup and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bibingka "rice flour cake"
directions: About the coconut:
I use 1 small can of Durkee coconut, but you can use freshly grated coconut.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; soak meat for about 1 hour.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pan with spoon just until blended well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still warm (not hot), frost with the following:

title: cranberry mold(excellent with turkey and chicken.)
directions: Note:
May use fresh cranberries with 3/4 cup sugar and 1 cup berries.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water; boil for about 10 minutes.
Add the sausage and red potatoes; boil for about 10 minutes.
Add the corn and boil 5 to 7 minutes.
Add shrimp and bacon; boil about 5 minutes (until shrimp are done). When done, drain water and serve in a large bowl.

title: sundae chocolate cups
directions: Combine over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate morsels and shortening.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth. Coat inside of each cupcake liner with chocolate mixture.
Place cupcake liner in hand.
Rotate gently, using rubber spatula to rush chocolate up sides.
Place in muffin pans.
Chill until firm.
When firm, peel off foil and return shells to muffin pan.
Chill until ready to serve.
Remove shells to serving plate.
Fill with scoop of ice cream.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Garnish with fruit.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and milk together.
Set aside.
Cream together the cream cheese, pudding mixture and confectioners sugar.
Using an 8-inch clay pot, spread small amount of pudding-cream cheese mixture in bottom and along sides of pot. Dust bottom and sides with cookie crumbs.
Beginning with cookie crumbs, put a layer of crumbs, followed by a layer of the pudding-cream cheese mixture, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers all the way to the top, putting the 1 1/2 cups of reserved cookie crumbs on top.
(You can stick a silk flower with green leaves in the middle of the pot.
Also, you can use a small garden hand spade as a serving utensil.)
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: beef-n-egg noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Put 1 tablespoon bacon drippings in frying pan. Brown onion.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper to frying pan. Cook.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat.
Cook and strain noodles and add to sauce mixture.
Grease large casserole with margarine.
Put a layer of sauce and noodles, then a layer of cheese.
Do this until all of sauce mixture is gone.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pecan layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 round 9 x 1- 1/2 inch round pans. Beat flour, sugar, shortening, buttermilk, egg yolks and vanilla in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds. Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 2 minutes. Beat in egg whites on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 2 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour into cake pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back up when touched lightly in the center. Cool 10 minutes, remove from pans. Cool completely. Fill layers and frost top and sides of cake with cream cheese pecan frosting. Garnish with pecan halves. Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off the juice from all the fruits.
Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook 1 to 3 hours in slow cooker (crock-pot).

title: mandarin cake
directions: Mix melted butter with sugar, eggs, juice of mandarin and then add the remaining ingredients.
Put in cake pan (size variable) and place in oven for 40 to 45 minutes (medium temperature).
When done, add powdered sugar on top.

title: chocolate worms
directions: Melt chips together in double boiler (or can microwave). Add peanuts and chow mein noodles. Mix to coat. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: frozen fruit salad for christmas
directions: Beat whipping cream with sugar until thickened.
Fold in mayonnaise and mashed bananas.
Add rest of ingredients; pour into pan and freeze.
Set pan out an hour before serving time.
Can be refrozen if not completely thawed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour into ready made pie crust.
Top pie with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Prepare pudding according to package directions using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Fold topping into prepared pudding.
Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Put on another layer of crackers, then remainder of pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then frost with chocolate icing (1 can of milk chocolate icing or Chocolate Glaze).

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water and add all other ingredients except sour cream.

Pour half of mixture into long dish and congeal. When this is congealed, spread sour cream over entire portion and then spread the remaining mixture of jello over the sour cream. Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: german green beans
directions: Fry finely diced bacon until brown and crisp; remove from skillet.
Cook onion in bacon fat until it is yellow and then stir in flour.
Add and bring to a boil the bean liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in beans; heat through and serve with crisp bacon on top.

title: squash custard pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except for the pie pastry and additional whipped cream. Pour into the pastry.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, bake for 45 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.
Chill.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Stew fryer.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Save broth for dressing.
Spread chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Mix dressing as the directions say.
Spread on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pie pumpkins
directions: Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken breasts with crab(pollo con granchi)
directions: Slice chicken breasts
into
8 pieces.
Heat butter and oil in large
skillet; add chicken pieces.
Saute lightly over medium heat.
Add
carrot
strips,
mushrooms
and
asparagus slices. Cook for
to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except crab. Continue
cooking,
stirring occasionally, until chicken is tender to fork,
10 to 15 minutes.
Add crab last 5 minutes, tossing lightly.
To
serve,
place chicken pieces on platter and spoon crab mixture on top.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
