directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash squash; trim ends and cut into thick slices.
Cook in small amount of boiling water (salted) for 10 minutes.
Drain and chop squash coarsely.
Put sausage and onion in skillet.
Cook until sausage is light brown.
Drain off fat (grease the casserole with a little of the fat).
Combine squash, sausage, crumbs, eggs, thyme, salt and half of cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff batter.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Let cool.
Make stuffing balls.
Wrap chicken around stuffing ball.
Place in dish.
Mix soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Put dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat egg.
Add milk and melted shortening.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients. Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill paper lined muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
While muffins are baking, melt 1/2 cup butter.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
While muffins are still hot, dip each in butter and then in cinnamon sugar.
Serve immediately.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Melt 1 pound cheese.
Stir in chili and salsa.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon-buttered spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain.
Stir in margarine and lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: In each quart jar place 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill. Pour hot solution of water, vinegar and salt into jars packed with uncut cucumbers, garlic and dill.
Seal with heated lids and rings.
Must set 6 weeks before using.

title: sixty-minute yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; place bowl in pan of water (98°).
Let rise 15 minutes.
Shape; cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425 ° approximately 15 minutes.
Brush with butter while hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mama lee's chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery until tender in 2 cups water and margarine.
Mix other ingredients in order given.
Stir well.
Bake in a well greased baking pan to desired brownness.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place rounded teaspoonful in cup of boiling water. Store in airtight jar.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain well.
Stir in taco sauce and continue to heat until hot.
Remove from heat.
Toss together lettuce, pepper, tomato, cheese and chips.
Spoon hot beef mixture over salad ingredients.
Add salad dressing tossing all ingredients well.
Serve immediately.

title: potato wedges
directions: Combine butter, catsup, mustard, paprika and salt; mix well. Cut potatoes into quarters lengthwise; slash each wedge crosswise at 1/4-inch intervals, but do not cut through skin.
Place potatoes, skin side down, on baking sheet.
Brush with 1/3 of butter mixture.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender, basting with butter mixture.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together with hand mixer. Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.

title: jello salad
directions: Put jello (no water) in bowl and add all other ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: spaghetti
directions: Mix thoroughly first 8 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Fry in melted butter (open pan); turn over with care.
Remove from pan. Add 1 large can of tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti in salted, boiling water 12 minutes.
Drain.
Add meat balls to spaghetti sauce and pour over spaghetti.
Good reheated.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown meat with onions
and
bell peppers.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add few drops of Tabasco sauce.
Cook over medium heat on top of stove for 1 hour. This recipe halves easily and freezes well.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, put thawed broccoli, then put diced, cooked chicken over broccoli.
In a bowl, mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread over chicken and broccoli to the edges of the pan.
Sprinkle cheese over the casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir butter, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips or peanut butter chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 4-cup container, uncovered, using High cycle and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Heat milk in 2-cup glass container, uncovered for 2 minutes.
Stir milk and flour mixture until smooth.
Add salt and pepper; cook, uncovered, for 6 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir twice during cooking time in 2-quart micro-type casserole.
Combine potatoes, onions and white sauce. Cover with wax paper and cook for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender, sprinkle with paprika.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 pan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar, making sure butter is soaked into sugar and spread evenly.
Add pineapple and juice; spread evenly.
Add cake mix that is mixed to package directions.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: french-toasted sandwich
directions: Place turkey or ham on 4 of the bread slices; top each with second slice.
Halve each sandwich diagonally.
In a shallow dish beat eggs and water until combined.
Dip sandwiches into egg mixture.
Grill on griddle or lightly greased skillet over medium heat about 2 to 3 minutes each side.
Place 2 of the sandwich halves in each of 4 individual shallow casseroles, overlapping slightly; set aside.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash chili peppers well.
Then blanch them or scald them over open flame to peel the outer layer of skin.
Peel them completely. Cut a hole in the top of the pepper for stuffing them.
Then scrape out the seeds inside, being careful not to get them on your hands -- they burn!!
Let them cool.
Meanwhile, brown the ground beef and add raisins and pecans to the meat, cooking it for just a few minutes.
Then stuff the chili peppers with the meat mixture.
Beat your egg and roll chili peppers in the egg.
Then roll them in the flour and fry them in oil in a skillet turning them from sided to side until crispy on outside.
Serve them covered in diced tomatoes or stewed tomatoes (some people eat them plain with no tomatoes).

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth, add cooled melted margarine and flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
You must have a pizzelle iron.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with water and raisins, if used.

title: broccoli-stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place half of broccoli in pan, then all the stuffing.
Top with remaining broccoli.
Mix the 2 cans of soup together; do not add water.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Arrange chicken, breast side up, in dish.
Sprinkle with thyme and pepper. Combine soup and water. Spoon over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove foil halfway through cooking.
Stir sauce before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash, trim and thinly slice the broccoli, cauliflower, celery and pepper crosswise.
Dice red onion and green onions small; drain olives, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cut mushrooms smaller; quarter the water chestnuts.
Mix vegetables in large bowl with lid that seals tight.
Mix Italian dressing and 3 packages dressing mix together well; pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover salad tightly.
Let marinate for at least 12 hours, turning occasionally.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the popped corn and nuts.
Melt butter, oil and marshmallows over medium heat. Pour over corn and nuts. Stir until well coated. Add the M&M's.
Stir into mixture.
Pack well into greased tube pan.
Put in refrigerator at least 1 hour or until cold. Turn out and slice.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water and set aside. Heat soup until boiling. Add cream cheese to soup and stir until dissolved. Then add gelatine, mayonnaise, celery, onions and shrimp. Grease mold with mayonnaise and pour mixture in. Let chill overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling; spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix into cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: In casserole dish, put 8 ounces cream cheese on bottom, then the chili and green chilies.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese. Bake at 325° until bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: overnight fruit bowl
directions: Section oranges.
Drain and cut in half.
Mix fruit.
Fold in yogurt.
Spoon into pie pan.
Cover and freeze overnight.

title: not hard, not fattening, not expensive, not bad chicken
directions: Select your favorite pieces of chicken.
Sprinkle both sides with favorite seasoning: lemon pepper and garlic salt, or curry and tarragon, or just salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a little flour in the bottom of as many pans as you need and put in chicken, skin side down.
Pour in boiling water that has been seasoned with stock or bouillon cubes until the chicken pieces are almost covered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn pieces over, sprinkle with paprika and bake another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit, mix with jello, cottage cheese, marshmallows and cool whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: miracle peach cobbler
directions: Mix all except peaches and margarine.
Melt margarine in skillet, then pour mixed ingredients into melted butter in skillet.
Add peaches; pour off syrup.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: maui muffins
directions: Mash bananas in bowl.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix, then add bran, buttermilk, oil, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir to blend.
Add flour and stir to moisten; do not overbeat.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In two 2-quart or one large baking dish, put layer of coarsely chopped chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and sherry and season to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with poppy seed.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening.
Spread lightly with prepared mustard.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Arrange chops, standing up, surrounded by stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: *Or use 3 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Place all of the above ingredients into a large pot and bring to a rapid boil.
Lower heat to medium low and cover with lid. After 30 minutes, turn chicken over and cook on the other side for an additional 30 minutes.
After one hour (total) cooking, taste the sauce and adjust to your liking.
If sauce is too salty, add more sugar.
If sauce is too sweet, add a bit of soy sauce.
You know the chicken is done when it is just about falling off the bone.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Peel and boil one small potato until soft enough to mash with a fork.
Then add confectioners sugar to the mashed potatoes, until it can be formed into a ball.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Re-roll and cut.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water a few minutes.
Combine onion, pepper and carrots.
Combine everything else and boil until sugar dissolves.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.
Better if made 3 or 4 days in advance.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls into an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing over crust.
Top with cut up vegetables such as cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, fresh mushrooms, green peppers, black or green olives and tomatoes. Grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Cut into squares.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Cream oleo with sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition. Drop by large teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar. Bake about 12 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg.
Add flour, soda and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pan.
Mix 1 stick butter and 1 cup corn flakes together and spread over the top of the mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Saute onions
and pepper in butter.
Mix in sour cream; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Pour
sour
cream mixture on top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar; add egg, beating well.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Combine flour and spices, add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in apple butter and chopped pecans. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and five minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes then remove to wire rack, and cool completely.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Pierce cake with large fork 1/2-inches apart.
Mix boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Carefully pour 1/2 of gelatin over one cake layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Dip cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Unmold on serving plate.

title: seasoned spinach balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on 2 ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter, then add seasonings.
Place remaining ingredients in a larger roaster or baking pan and pour butter mixture over all.
Mix well, then bake in oven, stirring occasionally.
Set oven at 250° and bake about 2 1/2 hours or until crisp.
Makes about 8 quarts.

title: spaghetti in oil sauce
directions: In saucepan, put in first 5 ingredients.
Saute until onion is golden; add rest of ingredients except spaghetti.
Cook about 10 minutes and pour over spaghetti.

title: pureed squash sory
directions: Cover squash and water in saucepan. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes. Puree top with scallions.

title: vegetable garden primavera(serves 8)
directions: Cook linguine to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, cook the squash, broccoli, asparagus and carrots in a small amount of boiling salted water until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain. In a saucepan, combine light cream, basil and pepper; bring to a gentle boil.
Boil for 8 to 10 minutes, or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.
Toss together linguine, vegetable mixture, cream mixture and Parmesan cheese.

title: texas dessert
directions: Prepare the chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding as directed. Set aside and let cool.
Press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan a mixture of the flour, pecan pieces and melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: command performance corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix corn, milk and melted butter together.
Combine all ingredients and add slightly beaten eggs. Pour into a well buttered 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir once after the first 25 minutes of baking time. Corn pudding should be firm and slightly browned when done.
This is really a wonderful side dish.
Serves at least 8.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Divide icing into 2 parts.
Color one part red (to look like ketchup) and the other part yellow (to look like mustard).
Spread red icing on bottom of one vanilla wafer and yellow icing on the bottom of second vanilla wafer.
Sprinkle coconut on one half. Sandwich mint cookie between wafers to look like hamburger.
Brush small amount of egg white on top of "bun" and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: johnnycake(cornbread to some.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and set aside.
Pour vinegar into measuring cup.
Add milk and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt.
Make a well in the center and pour in eggs and butter.
Add soda to milk.
Stir and add to mixture in the bowl.
Mix well. Pour into greased pan or muffin tins.
Bake about 25 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes clean or top is lightly browned.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and egg yolks. Fold whipping cream into creamed mixture.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with 1/2 of cake; spread with layer of 1/2 creamed mixture and 1/2 of candy and nuts.
Repeat.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: picadilly strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and food coloring.
Boil over medium heat.
Place strawberries in baked, cooled crust.
Pour hot mixture over strawberries.
Let cool.
Top with whipped cream. Garnish with strawberries.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in 2 tablespoons of shortening.
Place rice in a long, 7 1/2 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Pour orange juice over rice and arrange your pork chops on top of rice.
Stir soup and pour it on top.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Bring butter, milk and peanut butter to a boil.
Remover from heat and add powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Ice cake while warm not hot.

title: manicotti with four cheeses
directions: In a saucepan melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Stir over low heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Cook manicotti shells according to package directions.
Drain and cover with cold water.

title: chicken liver spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Brown chicken livers in butter.
Cut in small pieces.
Add together with next 6 ingredients.
Then add olive oil.
Cook spaghetti for 7 minutes. Drain and put layer of spaghetti, then layer of meat sauce, alternate after each addition, ending with sauce.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: low-fat granola cereal
directions: Heat applesauce and honey together until hot.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix hot liquid with dry ingredients.
Place in two baking pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat in 200° oven for approximately 6 hours.
Serve with fruit and milk.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef in bottom of shallow casserole dish.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each chicken breast; arrange over beef. Spread undiluted soup over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Increase heat to 350° and bake for another 20 to 30 minutes, basting several times.
Delicious.

title: pork and potato main dish
directions: Brown pork steak and put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Slice preboiled potatoes on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup and chunks of cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Prepare 9 x 12 inch cake pan by greasing and flouring the sides.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Put sugar and butter in pan and bring to boil.
Pour sugar mixture in cake pan and arrange pineapple slices on top of sugar mix.
Put cherries in center of pineapple slices.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 50 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool 5 minutes, and turn upside down on cake plate.

title: mom's no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Rapidly boil, stirring often for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 3 cups quick cooking oatmeal, 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or lightly buttered tray.
Let stand until cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a large cookie sheet, making a solid dough. Bake.
Mix together the cream cheese, salad dressing and Hidden Valley.
Spread on cooled baked crust.
Sprinkle the following on top:
shredded carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, mushrooms, green onions and shredded cheese.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and onion and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over vegetables.
Mix mushroom soup, egg and mayonnaise together and spoon over vegetables. Combine crackers, cheese and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread over cabbage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake icing
directions: Put the amount of marbles you want to crack in a heavy kettle. Cat's eye marbles are safer to use.
Put kettle over heat, not on full high on a gas stove from 3 to 5 minutes.
Take kettle to sink and turn on cold water over marbles to crack them.
Protect your eyes, as some may shatter up.
Drain.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small chunks.
Cut onion in half. Put onion and egg in blender.
Blend on "grate" setting for 20 seconds.
With blender still running drop pieces of potato into blender.
Blend about 20 seconds after last piece of potato is added.
Transfer mixture to a bowl.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper and parsley.
Stir.

title: pecan kiss cake
directions: Beat egg whites (at room temperature) in a medium mixing bowl until foamy; add sugar, 2 teaspoons at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla and pecans.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 55 minutes.
Remove from waxed paper and cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: green salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: turkey soup(leftover turkey)
directions: Melt butter and saute
onion,
carrots and celery until celery and
onion are limp and transparent.
Add chopped green peppers, apples,
tomato juice, turkey stock, flour and water mixed,
curry powder,
nutmeg, whole cloves, salt and pepper. Simmer until
all vegetables
are done.
It can go for hours, but should simmer
at least
1/2 to 2 hours on low simmer. Remove cloves and add cooked rice and turkey. Heat thoroughly. Makes 8 to 10 generous servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool and slice very thin.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and celery seed.
Fry cut bacon until done, but not brown.
Saute onion.
Add flour and sugar; blend.
Add vinegar and water; stir until thickened.
Pour over potatoes, mixing well. Serve well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil; pour over flour.
Mix and stir until moist.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: korean beef
directions: Mix all ingredients into large bowl. Add steak. Stir, mixing very well. Put in refrigerator and let it stay 2 to 3 days. Take it out about twice a day, stirring it well. Grill steak after marinating 3 days. Serve with baked potato and Texas toast. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: southern chicken roll-ups
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness. Place a cheese slice on each; roll up jelly roll style. In a shallow bowl, combine flour and pepper. Add chicken and roll to coat. In a skillet over medium heat, cook chicken in butter until browned, about 10 minutes, turning frequently. Add broth and oregano; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 12 to 14 minutes
or until chicken juices run clear.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine
cheese and croutons in the bottom of a greased 10 x 6
x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients
and mix until blended.	Pour over crouton mixture.
Cook bacon	until crisp.
Crumble and sprinkle over mixture.	Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: sour tea biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill miniature muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 350° until light brown in color.
Makes about 25 to 30.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken in Italian dressing over night.
Keep Refrigerate.
Mix equal parts of flour and parmesan cheese.
Add garlic and salt to taste.
Roll chicken in flour mixture and put in shallow baking pan.
Pour remaining dressing around chicken, but not on top.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Gradually add sugar to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla, nuts and crackers.
Mix well and bake in buttered pie plate 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate coconut marshmallow pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the coconut, butter and pecans. Press onto bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend all ingredients, except butter in a bowl.
Put butter on top of mixture.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
When done, mix until smooth.

title: cream tacos
directions: Mix together cooked hamburger, Ro-Tel, Velveeta, beans and chili in crock-pot. Stir thoroughly and
heat until bubbling. (Time will vary depending on your crock-pot.) Thirty minutes before you get ready to serve, shake whipping cream well and pour into hot mixture.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet. Add zucchini, onion, garlic and green pepper. Saut 10 minutes, until softened. Transfer to a saucepan and add tomatoes and spices. Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes. Stir in beans and cook 10 more minutes. Serve over rice and serve garnished with cheese or sour cream.

title: kabobbed grilled shrimp
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into a bowl.
Set aside pineapple chunks with shrimp and mix until coated.
Alternate pineapple chunks and shrimp on skewers.
Cook on preheated grill for about 2 minutes on each side or until done to your preference.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Can be used as a salad or a dessert.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Dice eggplant.
Saute with onion and pepper.
Lightly beat egg in casserole.
Add eggplant mixture, mushroom soup and milk. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° until done.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Pour mixture over vegetables. Cover and chill for 8 hours. Makes 10 servings.

title: festive holiday pie
directions: Fold together all
ingredients and pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: frosted delights
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift
together
dry
ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and mix.
Spread thinly on a baking sheet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll ball in crushed nuts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine and bring to a boil the cornstarch, sugar and water. Add jello.
When cool, add 6 cups strawberries.
(Makes enough to fill 2 pies.)
Top with Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned chicken pot pie
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with chicken and eggs.
Melt oleo in heavy skillet and stir in flour.
Cook a few minutes, but do not brown.
Add broth and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over eggs and chicken in casserole.
Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Heat small amount of oil in wok.
Cook some slices of garlic for a few minutes.
Add some pieces of each color pepper and onion.
Cook 1 minute.
Add 2 to 3 shrimp, pour 1/4 cup beer and allow shrimp to turn pink.
Sprinkle with spices.
Remove.
Serve on thin slice of bread.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to pumpkin mixture; blend well.
Stir in chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coffeecake(fellowship hour)
directions: Cream together in order given, except pie filling.
Spread into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cake pan sprayed with cooking spray, keeping 1 cup batter out.
Dab pie filling on top and remaining batter on top of filling.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Drizzle thin mixture of 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, 3 to 4 tablespoons milk and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract on top.

title: sausage balls(finger food)
directions: Mix and form in small balls (about the size of walnuts).
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ice cream(for 1 gallon)
directions: Put the sugar, whipping cream and eggs all together, then add the milk. After adding the sugar, whipping cream, eggs and milk, add cherries. Put in ice cream maker. Freeze when done.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger, sausage and garlic until done. Add tomato puree and simmer 1 hour.
Chill overnight.
Mix cottage cheese, egg, parsley and Ricotta cheese. Chill overnight.
Cook noodles until half done.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the sauce, noodles, sauce, cottage cheese mixture, cheese and noodles. Repeat.
Cook 1 hour or 45 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Chop all fruit and nuts. Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift all flour, salt, cinnamon and soda together. Add flour and vanilla.
Gradually stir in all fruit and nuts. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Mix dry ingredients with liquids, stirring only enough for batter to be smooth.
Dip rings into batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep fat (375°).
Drain on brown paper bag.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Serve immediately or keep warm in oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: block party bean bake
directions: Brown beef.
Drain fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into roasting pan.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls #2
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves that have been in boiling water long enough to be limp.
Place in roaster. Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Heat tomato sauce, tomato soup and 1 Tbsp. Worcestershire.
Pour over cabbage rolls. Bake, covered for another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes(makes 24 cupcakes)
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients with your hands.
Save 1 cup for crumbs.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture into flour mixture.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full with batter.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed jumbo pasta shells and marinara sauce
directions: Cook shells until just tender.
Combine all ingredients except Mozzarella cheese and shells.
Mix all together; stuff shells. Top with Marinara Sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian veggies
directions: Steam string beans (or veggie of choice) for 5 minutes and drain.
Heat oil in pan and saute vegetables for three minutes. Add bread crumbs, cheese and pepper.
Toss together well.
Top with fresh basil.

title: mexican sweet potatoes
directions: Toss all vegetables together and fry in butter until potatoes are brown and crisp.
Salt to taste.
A delicious way to use leftover sweet potatoes!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, pineapple, nuts, salt and sugar.
Make 3 layers of potato mixture with marshmallows between layers.
Top with bits of butter and more sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deviled green beans(microwave)
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish, combine margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and black pepper.
Cook on High 30 seconds.
Add green beans.
Mix well to combine.
Evenly sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Serves 4.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Roll meat in flour mixture and brown in olive oil.
Take stewed tomatoes and drain, but keep the juice; set tomatoes aside.
To the juice, add onion, garlic, Kitchen Bouquet and about 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour over meat and simmer, covered, for about an hour.
Add peppers, cut into strips, for another 15 minutes and then add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce and cook for another 5 or more minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Remove flowerets from broccoli and set aside.
Peel stalks and cut into thin slices. Coat chicken with 1 tablespoon of stir-fry sauce.

title: five hour stew
directions: Just mix all together, then stir occasionally.
Bake 5 hours at 250° in a covered pan.
Real good!

title: sourdough bread
directions: For starter, mix potato flakes, sugar and 1 cup water and let sit out all day.
Add oil, salt and 1 1/2 cups warm water and let sit out all night.
Next morning, add flour and work up with hands to form round ball.
Let rise until double in size. Separate into 2 balls and form into 2 loaves.
Place into greased pans and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak strips in hot Wesson oil, add bouillon, peppers, onion, celery and cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Cook over low heat in covered fry pan for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, pumpkim pie spice, Milnot and pumpkin in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts on top. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour chicken(for a quick supper this recipe is great!)
directions: Put spaghetti in a pot.
Oh, and put in water.
Put tomatoes in it sometimes.
Put sauce in a bowl.
Add cooked meat.
This is how you make the spaghetti!

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and oil until sugar dissolve.
Let cool. Mix all other ingredients.
Pour dressing over and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep for a long time.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix peaches and lemon juice.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon; stir into peaches.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Dot butter on top. Top with pie crust.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk(for baking)
directions: Blend until milk is dissolved. Chill; keep in covered container in refrigerator.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook onions in margarine in a large saucepan until onions are tender, but not brown.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook, covered, over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Add soup and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Do not boil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stir-pak-pour cake
directions: Mix cake mix as it says on box.
Cook cake.
While it cools, mix up jello, poke holes in cake and fill each hole.
Put Cool Whip over cake and cherry filling on top of that.
Cut and serve!

title: neil's after dinner delight
directions: Put vodka, creme de menthe and Kahlua in large tulip glass or brandy snifter.
Pour coffee over the alcohol and stir.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, covered.
Take cover off the last 5 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Fold all ingredients into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven (350°). Immediately turn off oven and leave cookies overnight.
Guaranteed not to burn!

title: mixed garden salad
directions: Drain vegetables, cover with dressing and refrigerate.
Keeps very well for long periods of time.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach briefly and drain.
Mix egg and milk.
Add spinach and cheese.
Mix, adding salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with additional cheese.
Broccoli may be substituted for spinach.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange ingredients in listed order in buttered casserole. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Cool and add 1 pint of Miracle Whip.

title: easy popcorn haystacks
directions: Combine popcorn and chow mein noodles in a large bowl.
Place butterscotch morsels in a glass bowl.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 5 minutes or until melted, stirring midway.
Pour over popcorn-noodle mixture.
Stir to coat well.
Drop by heaping tablespoonsful on wax paper until firm.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 24.

title: jewish rye dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and set aside.
Scoop out a good sized hole in bread and put the dip in hole.
Break up scooped out bread and use to dip.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Wrap chicken around dried beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken and secure with toothpick.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a heavy medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cook for two more minutes, while stirring constantly, while mixture continues to boil.
Add peanut butter, then remove from heat.
Stir in the oatmeal and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until cool.
Serve.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Mix juice from cherries and pineapple with enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring to boil, then dissolve jello in mixture. Pour in Coke (mixture will foam).
Put in refrigerator to thicken. Cut cream cheese into small pieces.
When jello has thickened, add fruit, nuts and cream cheese.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Serve with Cool Whip as dessert or with sour cream as salad.

title: oven french fries
directions: You will need vegetable cooking spray.

title: beef broccoli
directions: Bring water to a boil in a saucepan.
Add broccoli flowerets and cook until done.
Remove from heat; drain.
Rinse under cold water to chill.
Drain well and set aside.

title: bohemian dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook with stew or any boiled meat.
Cook for 3 minutes without removing cover.
Remove from heat; let stand, covered, another 5 minutes.

title: lollipops
directions: Place 42 lollipop sticks, 4-inches apart, on greased sheets or foil.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together the first three ingredients.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Continue cooking without stirring until small amounts of mixture are dropped into very cold water and becomes hard brittle threads.
Cool slightly.
Stir in flavor and food color just enough to mix.
Drop candy mixture from tip of teaspoon over one end of each stick to form 2-inch circle.
(If mixture hardens before all lollipops are made, stir over low heat just until mixture is melted.)
Makes 42 lollipops.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoon of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients except pretzels.
Place pretzel pieces onto a cookie sheet; sprinkle combined seasoning over them.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Toss and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: minced onion cream cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and Minced onion medley seasoning blend. Mix well and refrigerate at least one hour prior to serving. Great with you favorite vegetables.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk.
Stir in potatoes and next 3 ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is thickened and potatoes are done.
Yields 5 cups.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover chicken completely until chicken is done. Remove chicken from broth and cool. Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening. Add enough water to make a good dough. Roll out on floured dough board to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut in 1-inch squares. Drop squares one at a time into boiling broth and cook until dough is done. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit and cheese salad
directions: Make graham cracker crust.
Crush graham crackers to crumbs. Add 3 tablespoons sugar (mix); add 1/3 cup butter.
Spread in the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Cool completely before doing next step.

title: cheese 'n wiener crescents
directions: Cut 4 cheese slices into 6 strips each.
Slit wieners to within 1/2 inch of ends and insert 3 cheese strips.
Center wiener on a Pillsbury crescent dinner roll and roll up.
Place on a baking sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk.
Cook until boiling and sticky.
Pour in egg yolks, then pour back in pan. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: betty's beef casserole
directions: Put all in a casserole.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve in a patty shell or over rice.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter, add squash.
Simmer until tender. Drain and add sour cream, cheese and salt, stirring over low heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Add beaten egg yolks, chives and bacon.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Brown at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add margarine, milk, corn syrup and salt.
Heat to a boil, stirring often.
Boil vigorously 3 minutes, stirring often.
Cool then add vanilla.
Great on ice cream!

title: apple crisp
directions: Sprinkle applesauce with cinnamon.
Mix together the following and pour over applesauce:
butter, brown sugar, flour and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, and egg. Add dry ingredients, zucchini, fruits, and nuts; mix well. Let set overnight; drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: kashi's tuna on white
directions: Put tuna fish in a bowl and mix it with the mayonnaise.
When that's done, put the tuna fish on the bread.
You can put lettuce if you want.
Then take a knife and cut in half or fourths and eat. "Enjoy!"

title: whipped topping
directions: Take a cup of kindness, mix it well with love.
Add a lot of patience and faith in God above.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly graham cracker crumbs, granulated sugar and melted butter.
Press half the crumb mixture evenly in bottom of square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
In small mixer bowl, beat 1/2 cup margarine and the confectioners sugar until light and fluffy. Spread evenly over crumbs in pan.

title: fried squash
directions: Cook and mash 3 to 4 cups squash. Mince 1 onion. Beat 1 egg. Add to squash. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and salt and pepper to taste. Add enough self-rising flour to make a thick batter. Drop by spoonfuls in hot grease. Cook until brown.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil hen until tender in water seasoned with 1 onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces. Reserve stock.
Combine soups and grated cheese.
Just before assembling casserole, soak the tortillas in boiling chicken stock until softened.
Start layering casserole in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish in this order:
softened tortillas, chicken, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle to taste with garlic salt and chili powder; add soup mixture.
Repeat the layers.
Cover the casserole with undrained tomatoes.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix together cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper and sour cream until smooth; set aside.

title: country chicken
directions: Place ham in bottom of pan.
Lay chicken on top of ham.
Mix soup, half and half and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Mix cheeses together and sprinkle over the top and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 325° and bake for 1/2 hour, uncovered, to brown.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, sugar, vanilla, food coloring and nuts, if desired.
Add 7-Up. Chill until set.
Stir when partially set to keep nuts from coming to top.

title: molded festal salad(serves 12+)
directions: You will need an 11-cup ring mold.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients listed, except ginger ale. Chill until ready to serve. Add ginger ale, frozen cherries or strawberries if desired.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Beat together and spread over brownies.
Refrigerate.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Pour cereals into large bowl; set aside.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large resealable bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 9 cups.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown ground chuck with diced onion.
Drain grease from meat. Add mushrooms to meat and cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients, salt and pepper to taste; simmer.
Boil spaghetti in water with garlic oil and salt; drain.
Serve spaghetti with meat sauce.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add all other ingredients (do not drain cans) and cook until hot.

title: potatoes and chicken santa fe
directions: While potatoes cook in large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add salsa and corn; toss until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chile rellano casseroleroswell, new mexico
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
Add layer of green chilies, cooked, split, face up.

title: stuffed turkey legs
directions: In 8 x 12-inch deep pan, put wine, oil, water and paprika. With bone saw, cut off 2 to 3 inches of bone off legs.
Stuff legs with garlic and peppers.
Season and wrap with bacon.
Place in pan and cover tight with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes longer.
Serve with dressing (rice or cornbread), snap bean casserole, hot brandy peaches and French bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in boiling water until fork-tender.
Drain. Add cracker crumbs to squash.
Add butter, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs lightly with evaporated milk.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes, until medium dry.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and shortening until well blended. Stir in 2 cups baking mix and oats until crumbly.
Press half of mixture in pan.
Bake until set, about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: *I buy a bag of cranberries and keep in the freezer for when needed.

title: easy caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Go to your local Target Store and get Act II microwave caramel popcorn.
It consists of a bag of popcorn and pouch of caramel. until it is 2 to 3 seconds between pops. up, then spread out on cookie sheet.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler; set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Put half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and add chocolate chips and then caramel mixture.
Crumble on remaining batter and bake for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: spicy meat pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir in gradually.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Put into 8-inch pie crust and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Starter:
Put in 1 gallon jug; keep lid loose and mark all your dates on calender.

title: shane's favorite meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into twenty 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan in 400° oven until light brown 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O as directed and chill.
When slightly thickened, add pineapple.
Pour into 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Mix mayonnaise and softened cream cheese, then add nuts and spread over molded Jell-O.
Chill until firm.
Prepare strawberry Jell-O and mix with cranberry sauce.
Pour over previous mixture. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan over medium flame, bring rice and water to a boil.
Simmer over low flame, covered, until rice is very tender and most of the water is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir into hot rice with half and half.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Turn off flame; stir in butter and vanilla.
In small bowl, slightly beat egg yolks; gradually stir in about 1 cup of hot rice mixture; stir back into remaining rice mixture.
Stirring often, cook over medium flame just until mixture starts to bubble. Let stand at room temperature and serve warm.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix pudding mix and 1 cup brown sugar. Put rolls in bottom of pan and sprinkle with 1/2 the pudding mix and sugar.
Put another dozen frozen rolls and sprinkle on the other 1/2 of sugar mix.
Over this, sprinkle another 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Leave uncovered overnight and bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream together flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan over bottom and part way up the sides.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix together eggs, lemon juice, sugar, flour and salt.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powder when cooled.

title: buttermilk corn bread loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 1/4 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Combine milk and cola in an ice cream churn.
Freeze it using an electric or hand churn.
Add small juice size pina colada mix or smallest can of crushed pineapple, drained well.

title: glazed fruit-fruit filled drop biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees. Lightly grease cookie sheet. Bisquick mix, butter and sugar in medium bowl until crumbly. Stir in milk until dough forms; beat 15 strokes. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet. Make a shallow well in center with the back of spoon dipped in water; fill each with 1 teaspoon of preserves. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. drizzle with Glaze while warm 1 dozen biscuits.

title: dressing
directions: Mix and bake first 5 ingredients to make cornbread. Mix all ingredients with cornbread and bake till brown. Can use
only 1 can of each soup.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease skillet or baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients and stir only until moist.
Bake in skillet 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: banana cake icing
directions: Mix banana and lemon juice together.
Cream butter with 1 cup of sugar,
then
add
banana and enough of the remaining sugar to make
mixture thick enough to spread.
This will make enough to cover tops and sides of 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Dice onion up real small; saute in butter. Pour both soups in onion mixture.
Pour in rice.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Brown and season beef with Cajun seasoning and salt to taste.
Pour off excess grease after browning well.
Add sauteed pepper, onion and garlic.
Add Ranch-style beans.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: pioneer picnic cookies
directions: Blend butter and shortening until smooth and fluffy. Add both sugars and cream well. Add eggs, beating well. Stir in vanilla. Mix dry ingredients and gradually add to batter. Add chocolate chips and nuts. Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets about 1-inch apart. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool briefly on baking sheet, then remove to cooling racks. Store in airtight container. Yields about 7 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix the margarine, pretzels and white sugar.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted margarine and eggs; beat until blended.
Add vinegar and flavoring.
Mix in coconut; pour into the pie shell of your choice.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: cranberry sauce for all occasions
directions: Combine cranberries, Sweet 'N Low, water and extract in saucepan.
Simmer until skins of berries pop open and sauce thickens.
Add applesauce and cinnamon and simmer again.
When thickened, divide evenly into 6 portions.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Remove skin from chicken. Rinse and dry thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper. Coat each piece in oil and dip in milk. Shake to remove excess liquid and roll in crumbs. Let stand briefly so coating

will adhere. Line a baking pan with foil for easy clean up. Coat foil lining with cooking spray. Place chicken pieces in pan so they do not touch. Bake 45 minutes or longer. Crumbs will form a crisp crust.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Remove skin and bones.
Tear or cut into bite size.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken, Doritos and 1 package or Monterey Jack cheese.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, Ro-Tel and milk.
Warm and pour over layers of chicken, Doritos and cheese.
Crumble Doritos and sprinkle on top.
Spread other package of Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Saute sausage in a skillet; drain well.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Put bread cubes in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put a layer of cheese, then a layer of sausage.
Pour milk and eggs over all.
Refrigerate until the next day.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix oats, 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar, soda, salt and oleo together.
Reserve 1 cup of the mixture; press remaining mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: 5-minute chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a skillet and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in the oatmeal. Stir until well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Press cream cheese into bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Press refried beans on top and cover with salsa.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hamburger steak and rice
directions: Make hamburger patties, 2 for each person, and brown in skillet; drain grease.
Put onion rings on top of each patty. Pour tomato sauce over patties in skillet.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat corn tortillas on both sides in hot skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Put cheese and onion on corn tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a cake pan.
Spread Tostitos salsa con queso on top.
Heat in a 375° oven for 25 minutes or until cheese on inside melts.

title: broiled parmesan rounds
directions: Combine cheese, onion and Miracle Whip.
Spread on rye bread. Place on cookie sheet and broil until light brown and bubbly. Makes approximately 40.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Place bread in pan in two rows, overlapping slices, putting ham between and over slices.
Distribute broccoli and cheese over and around the bread slices.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients if too stiff.
Add a little milk.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush 1 cup corn flakes.
Melt 1/4 to 1/2 cup margarine.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top of casserole and pour margarine over top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain well.
Add to Bisquick.
Mix water and soup together, then add to sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in muffin pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions.
Mix into a ball and spread flat on a greased pizza pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Mix together the cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread on cooled cookie.
Decorate the top with sliced fruits, being sure to dip fruits that will darken in pineapple juice.

title: mary jo's lemon chicken
directions: Slice chicken thin.
Let soak in milk for 10 minutes.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs together and coat chicken in bread crumbs mixture.
(You may also add extra garlic powder and parsley.) After breading chicken, place in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onions slowly.
Stir until meat is all in fine pieces.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour, slowly.

title: arkansas cookies
directions: Cream melted butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Pat onto a greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Break apart enough graham crackers to cover the bottom of a jelly roll tray.
Combine margarine and sugar in a pot, bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chopped pecans.
Spread over the graham crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.
When cool, break apart.
These are like Mexican pralines.

title: country quail fried
directions: Cut quail in halves.

Season with salt and pepper. In bowl, combine eggs, milk, flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat until batter is smooth. Dip quail in batter. Fry in deep fat heated to 365° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and salt; mix well. Slowly stir in beet liquid; blend to smooth mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until sauce is clear and thick. Add butter and beets and mix well.

title: opal's blackberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, spices, soda and cloves.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in blackberries until mixture is smooth.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour (or until done) in Bundt pan.

title: surprise potatoes
directions: Slice and peel potatoes. Cook until almost done. Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Top with butter, salt and pepper.
Put dressing mix on, then cream of mushroom soup.
Slice sausage and layer on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven until done.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and mushrooms. Cover with stuffing. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: modoc rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage, cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until crisp-tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add jalapeno, rice and sausage to the vegetables in large skillet. Add the bouillon and heat; simmer until water is absorbed.

title: english trifle
directions: In large glass bowl (deep), slice pound cake.
Place in bottom of
bowl.
Prepare
Jell-O
and
pour over pound cake. Mash pound
cake with fork.
Place in refrigerator until set. Mix pudding and pour over Jell-O.
Smooth flat.
Add Cool Whip on
top of
pudding.
Decorate as desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt ingredients together.
Chill.
Then make into balls about the size of walnuts and chill again.

title: baked chicken planks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake well.
Cut chicken into 1 inch strips; dip chicken in margarine and shake in bread crumb mixture. Place in Pyrex dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: christmas cider
directions: Place red hots in percolator and put apple juice in pot of percolator.
Perk until red hots have melted.
Can be easily doubled.

title: quick chicken
directions: Coat pan with Pam cooking spray.
Put over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken.
Cook 10 minutes, turning one time.
Add water, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain chicken and serve.

title: caramel cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan and 1 smaller pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans.
Increase heat to 400°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix sauces and melted butter.
Put pretzels, nuts and cereals in large baking pan.
Pour the sauces and butter over the cereals. Sprinkle the garlic and salt over all.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: homemade lasagne
directions: While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Add spaghetti seasoning, stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and Italian seasoning.
Cook until boiling; then simmer 5 minutes.
Drain noodles and rinse in cold water to prevent sticking.
Divide sauce into 3 sections in skillet.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add salt, shortening and sugar.
Then put soda in buttermilk.
Add yeast, egg and 1 cup of flour.
Let rise until doubled in size about 1 hour, covered.
Punch down and let rise again about 1 hour in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: elegant crab meat balls
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat; combine with remaining ingredients except bacon.
Mix well.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Wrap with bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Broil under medium heat until bacon is crisp, about 10 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine orange slices, condensed milk, coconut, pecans and orange extract in baking dish; mix well.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.
Stir in confectioners sugar.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 2 tablespoons beet liquid.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add vinegar and beet liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add beets and butter; heat.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Cut deboned breasts into nugget-sized pieces.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, herbs and salt.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine.
Roll in crumb mixture.

title: 3 day coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix and bake cake according to directions on box. Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans. When cake is done, divide each layer into 2 layers. Mix sour cream and 1 (12 ounce) package of coconut together in small mixing bowl. Spread this mixture between layers of the cake.

title: checkerboard salad(not really a checkerboard)
directions: You will also need three 8 or 9-inch cake or pie pans.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder, salt and sugar. Sift together 3 times.
Add butter.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla. Add to flour mixture.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Melt the brown sugar.
Stir until melted. Arrange pineapple slices attractively.
Pour batter mix over.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: granola ii
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix the honey and oil.
Combine dry and moist ingredients.
Divide and spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: indiana old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, flour, margarine and nutmeg until well blended.
Add cream, a little at a time, until it is well moistened.
Add remaining cream.
Stir well and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes to an hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all
vegetables together in large bowl.
Mix the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, water and pepper in a pan and bring to a boil. Pour over the vegetables.
Mix and chill.

title: cajun chicken salad
directions: Whisk mustard, 2 tablespoons oil, white wine and honey together for dressing.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss lettuce, tomatoes and onion together in medium bowl.
Divide salad between two plates.
Combine cayenne, paprika, pepper, chili powder, garlic powder and salt in small bowl.
Coat chicken with spice mixture. Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Add chicken and fry until just cooked and crusty on outside, about 4 minutes per side. Cut into thin strips and place on salad.
Spoon dressing over and serve.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut the olives and combine with the chicken and celery. Combine onion with the mayonnaise, soy sauce and lemon juice. Pour over chicken mixture and blend lightly.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: raw applesauce
directions: Place half of the apples and remaining ingredients in blender container.
Blend on high until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining apples.
Repeat.

title: bacon muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix together flour, butter, milk and egg.
Add bacon, cheese and onions.
If batter seems too thick, add a little more milk.
Spray muffin pan with Pam or grease.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and cook until celery is done.
Freezes well.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Add all other ingredients, including water if needed.
Cook in a heavy pot for about 2 hours.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, allspice, turmeric and sugar.
Beat egg with water and add to flour mixture.
Mix well to make a smooth batter.
Cut onions into rings 1/4-inch thick and mix with salt. Dip onion rings in batter, a few at a time.
Fry in deep fat heated to 360° until rings are browned and float to top of fat.
Remove rings from fat with slotted spoon. Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown or firm.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon of the sugar in 1/2 cup of the water.
Beat eggs, shortening, salt, rest of the sugar and the rest of the water.
Add yeast and water mixture.
Add flour after beating in the cup of potatoes.
Knead in all of the flour.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls or loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
You may keep dough in refrigerator several days.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips and nuts) at one time.
Sprinkle flour on nuts and chips and add last.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed for 2 1/2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and mix well.
Add syrup, butter and
vanilla.
Next,
add pecans.	Bake about 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on high for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Set aside to cool, about 15 minutes.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: creamed tuna
directions: In sauce pan melt butter and cornstarch. Add milk and tuna. Stir until thickened. Add peas and carrots (heated)
if desired. Serve over toast.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pierce meat and marinate overnight.
Great for outdoor grilling.

title: raisin-pumpkin flapjacks
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flours, baking powder, spice and salt. Whisk in milk, honey and oil, then egg yolk.
In small bowl, beat the egg white to form stiff peaks.
Fold into yolk mixture.
Gently mix in pumpkin, then raisins.
Coat nonstick griddle or large skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat over medium-low heat; with 1/3 cup measure portion batter on griddle.
Cook until lightly browned, about 4 minutes, turning once.
Makes 4 servings (12 flapjacks).

title: italian wedding cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add to it the remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes; cool.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
Mix confectioners sugar and a small amount of warm water.

title: sourdough biscuits(originally from oklahoma)
directions: Mix in morning.
Put in refrigerator.
Pinch off what you want and keep rest of dough in refrigerator, covered.
You can pinch off dough as you go.
Bake at biscuit temperature (425° to 450°).

title: black forest cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs and syrup.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice (stir with spoon) then add other ingredients.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion. Drain off grease. Line in a 9 x 13-inch pan chips and meat. Mix soup and milk together in a separate bowl and pour over meat. Add picante sauce and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Place Ricotta in mixer; whip for 3 minutes.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Then gradually add flour.
Pour mixture into 10-inch pie dish with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: Mix cream cheese, ground sugar, oil and food color.
Mix well. Using pastry bag, drop from star tip onto waxed paper.
Let dry at room temperature 36 to 48 hours.
If firmer mint desired, transfer to paper towel after 32 hours and dry an additional 12 hours.
Makes about 10 dozen for weddings, anniversaries or parties.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Cook together the first 6 ingredients until thick.
Cool completely and add the remaining ingredients.
Let stand for a few hours to blend.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add flour and mix.
Add lemon juice, grated rind and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
(Pillsbury pie crust works fine.)

title: mulled cider
directions: Boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.

title: cacoons
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in cacoons. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until done.
Seal in pint jars.
Very good in hot dishes or as barbecue sauce.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar and oil mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done in a greased and tubed pan.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake meat in oven for 1 hour.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip, mustard, garlic salt and horseradish.
Then in another bowl, grate 1 cucumber and press out liquid.
Grate onion and carrot and add to ingredients. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onion stems into bits.
Chop 1/2 package of corned beef into small pieces.
Combine with cream cheese.
Add celery salt to taste.
Roll into a ball.
Serve with Townhouse crackers.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well. Form mixture into 8 patties 3/4-inch thick. Spread crumbs on waxed paper.
Press patties gently into crumbs to coat.
Heat oil in large skillet and fry patties over medium heat 4 minutes per side until crisp.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for about 1 hour.
Bake or broil until chicken is cooked.
Drizzle with remainder of marinade while cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add layer of chicken in baking dish.
Pour 1 can cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Add herb dressing mix and other can of soup, mixed with chicken broth.

title: the refresher
directions: In a juice extractor, combine watermelon, oranges, grapefruit, apples and lemons.
Mix well.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.
Put in one gallon container.

title: banana cake
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Then add and beat the oleo, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas. Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs.
Beat altogether for 4 minutes. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corrina's butter cream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with electric mixer. Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often. When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry. Add milk and beat a medium speed until light and fluffy. Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until ready to use. For the best results, keep icing bowl in refrigerator when not in use. Refrigerate in an airtight container, this can be stored up to two weeks. Rewhip before using.

title: cocktail pecans
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl, stirring well. Add pecan halves to mixture, stirring gently to coat well.
Spread coated pecans in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1 inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 300° for 25/30 min, stirring frequently.
Drain pecans on paper towels; let cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: hot cheese appetizer
directions: Stir over heat in large boiler until cheese melts.
Add a little Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.
Remove and cover top with sliced almonds.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in large mixing bowl. Beat in honey and eggs until smooth. Sift flour, cinnamon and salt. Stir into butter mixture. Add oats, pecans, raisins and dates. Stir. Shape dough into 2-inch balls. Place 9 balls on each cookie sheet and flatten. Bake until lightly browned (about 15 minutes). Remove the cookies to racks to cool.

title: texas fried venison
directions: Cut up venison into serving pieces.
Mix flour and salt and pepper together.
Coat venison with mixture and brown in pan with margarine.
Add chopped celery and sliced onions.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes and cook, covered, 1 to 2 hours. Cook noodles, drain and serve with venison.

title: holly's favorite cookie-candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too sticky, add more coconut.
Roll into bite size balls.
These can be made in all colors, depending on what jello you use.
They give cookie trays a lot of color.

title: shrimp relish
directions: Put in a crock or china or glass bowl.
Refrigerate several days and enjoy.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Place sliced carrots in boiling salted water.
Cook about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add onion and pepper.
Set aside.
Mix tomato soup, oil, vinegar and sugar together.
Bring to boil.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate.
This will keep a month.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat separately and grind. Combine meat in pot and add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 5 minutes and serve.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Stir together all ingredients and chill several hours.
Flavor improves with storing.

title: potato chip cookies-crunchies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add chips and nuts; stir in flour.
With 1 tablespoon of dough, form balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick to package directions, adding grated cheese.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on garlic salt to taste.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mash cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients and beat well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's grape juice pies
directions: Mix ingredients and cook in saucepan.
Put in pie shells and top with meringue.
Makes 3 pies.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: In sauce pan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and salt until blended then gradually add broth.
